title: fried cauliflower
directions: Break cauliflower into medium size pieces; par boil (about 2 minutes).
Take out of boiling water; run cold water over cauliflower.
Let excess water drain off.
Mix in a bowl Parmesan cheese and cracker crumbs.
Roll cauliflower in mixture.
Melt butter in frypan and cook on low until golden brown.

title: manicotti
directions: Saute turkey and beef in oil until browned.
Drain well.
Add onion.
Add tomato paste, water, basil, oregano, salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Boil manicotti shells in salt water for 30 minutes; drain and wash with cold water.
Dry.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook meat reserving broth.
Cook rice according to directions. Cook onions in butter until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in flour.
Drain mushrooms, saving liquid.
Add to chicken broth to make 1 1/2 cups.
Gradually stir into flour mixture.
Add cream and stir until thick.
Add rice, mushrooms, cut up meat, pimento, parsley, salt and pepper.
Put into a 2-quart dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nanny's sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and nutmeg together; set aside.
Mix milk and lemon flavoring; set aside.
Cream butter until fluffy and add 3 eggs.
Alternate milk mix and flour mix to butter mixture until soft dough.
Make it thick enough to work with.

title: best beef goulash
directions: In a 4-quart microwavable casserole, combine beef, 2 cups water, onion soup mix, mushrooms, paprika and caraway seed. Cover with lid.
Cook in microwave at High for 10 minutes and at Low for 55 to 60 minutes.
Stir twice.
To complete: blend cornstarch with remaining 1/4 cup water until smooth.
Stir into dish.
Cook, uncovered, at Low for 3 minutes or until thickened. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: slimmer shake
directions: Combine ingredients in blender.
Run on high until smooth and well blended.
Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: tortillas casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Roll up tortillas with ground beef.
Lay in pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour on top of tortillas.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: yummy spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Beat whole eggs until fluffy. Combine all ingredients except crackers and margarine.
Pour spinach mixture into greased 7 1/2 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Mix cracker crumbs in melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of spinach mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Watch it disappear!!

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cut each chicken breast half crosswise into 2 pieces and place in shallow dish with onion.
Mix vinegar, 3 tablespoons olive oil, 1 3/4 teaspoons salt, garlic, herbs, paprika, pepper and pepper sauce in small jar.
Cover and shake to blend.
Pour over chicken. Refrigerate 2 hours or longer, spooning marinade over chicken occasionally.
Drain well and save marinade.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Place separated cabbage leaves in about 3 inches of water in covered Dutch oven; steam for 15 minutes or until soft and pliable.
Remove and cool enough to handle.
Mix all other ingredients, except sauce, in a bowl and mix well.

title: nanny's chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken breasts (which have been shaken in a bag with flour, salt and pepper) in margarine slowly until golden brown. While browning, add onion.
Take out chicken and place in one layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put sliced fresh mushrooms in chicken pan and brown, then scatter over chicken.
Put 2 cans cream of celery soup in first pan with 1 can milk and 1/4 cup Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until chicken and mushroom flavor is absorbed.

title: boiled cookies (old family recipe)
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to rolling boil. Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Makes a large number of cookies.
Store in refrigerator for freshness.

title: bacon, lettuce and tomato appetizer
directions: Combine lettuce, bacon and mayonnaise together.
Place on top of Triscuits, topping off with tomatoes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Cook the ingredients on medium.
After the relish begins to boil, cook for 20 minutes.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil; remove.
Add onion and pepper to oil; stir-fry for one minute.
Return chicken to pan.
Add broccoli, carrots, water chestnuts and Chinese vegetables.
Cover and let simmer until vegetables are tender, but not mushy.
Add dash of garlic.
Mix soy sauce and cornstarch; add to vegetable mixture and stir to coat vegetables.
Serve over rice or Chinese noodles. Serves 6.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Saute onion in butter in a saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer together 10 minutes, covered. (May be frozen.)

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole for 50 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Heat 1/2 cup of the chocolate chips and the margarine in heavy 1-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally, until melted.
Mix baking mix, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Spread in pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows, nuts and remaining chocolate chips.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until marshmallows are light brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into about 2-inch squares.
Makes 30 bars.

title: joy's orange salad
directions: Combine jello, Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Add well drained fruit. You may decorate the top with a few of the orange segments, cherries and nuts.
Chill for about an hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Put applesauce in bowl; add sugar, spices and oleo.
Cook raisins until puffy; drain.
Sift flour and soda together; add to other ingredients.
Put in a regular bread pan (8 1/2 x 5-inch); bake in slow oven (325°) for 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Ice with plain confectioners sugar icing.

title: apple ginger cake
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until apples are tender.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: goldie's creamy apple pecan pie
directions: In a small bowl mix the apple pie filling, brown sugar and cinnamon; stir in nuts.
Spread half the mixture in pie crust. Chill remaining mixture.
Pour milk and half and half into small mixing bowl.
Add vanilla pie filling mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, about one minute.
Fold in whipped topping. Spoon over apple mixture in pie crust.
Freeze for one hour or chill three hours before serving.
Garnish with reserved apple mixture and additional whipped topping, if desired.
This pie is good without letting it thaw completely.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cook for 70 minutes at 350°.

title: sunglow coconut cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter, margarine and eggs.
Add milk.
Blend well, then add flour and baking powder.
Mix well and then add vanilla and coconut.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot potato salad with bacon
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain.
When cool to touch, peel and cut into chunks.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels and crumble.
Measure bacon fat and add oil to make 1/2 cup and return to pan.
Slice scallion and cook in fat until softened. Add vinegar, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Bring to boil and cook 1 minute.
Immediately pour the entire contents of pan over potatoes and toss to coat.
Add crumbled bacon.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: split-pea soup
directions: Cover peas with 2 quarts cold water and soak overnight or simmer gently for 2 minutes.
Then soak 1 hour.
Add ham bone, onion and seasonings.
Bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer (don't boil) 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bone. Cut off meat and dice.
Return meat to soup, add vegetables. Cook slowly, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes.
Salt to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cream cheese and sausage appetizers
directions: Spread 1 container of crescent rolls on a flat pan. Bake according to directions until barely brown. Fry sausage and drain well. Blend cream cheese in with sausage. Spread cream cheese and sausage mixture over crescent rolls. Lay second container of crescent rolls on top. Bake at 350° until golden brown. Cut into small squares.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Mix together onion and grated potatoes.
Grate potatoes with cheese grater.
Heat skillet until hot.
Add butter.
Immediately add potatoes and onion in pancake shape.
Brown.
Serve hot with syrup.

title: hucklebucks(whoopie pies)
directions: Cream together shortening, eggs, cocoa, vanilla and sugar. Add milk alternately with sifted dry ingredients, mixing after each addition until smooth.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in a 350° oven for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs. Stir soda into applesauce.
Reserve 1 cup flour to dredge fruit and nuts. Sift the remaining dry ingredients.
Add to the creamed mixture alternately with applesauce. Add nuts, fruit and preserves.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 3 hours. Cool.
Put in closed container and lay apples slices on top or place a small glass of wine in middle of cake for moisture.

title: mandarin consomme
directions: Boil, cut and drain the spinach and add it to the clear soup. Broil the mochi.
Place the mochi and several slices of kamaboko and some spinach into the bottom of bowls.
Pour the clear, hot soup (over all) into each bowl and serve.

title: breakfast sausage pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook sausage; crumble and drain.
Line pie crust with cheese.
Add sausage and cover with remaining cheese.
Mix eggs, salt, pepper and milk.
Pour over cheese and sausage.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients.
Mix with electric mixer 3 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in greased and floured pans at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool entirely before adding cream cheese frosting or serve hot from oven without frosting.

title: crackling bread
directions: Mix all together with tap water until desired mixture.
Pat into desired pones and place in greased pan or spider.
Cook in oven for 45 minutes at 450°.
Pour off excess grease and brown top with oven on broil (until desired brownness).

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg alternately with milk.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
After baking, roll in melted margarine and then in cinnamon-sugar.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed.
Top with black olives and/or chopped tomatoes, if desired.
Serve with chips.

title: cucumber salad dressing
directions: Add the sugar and vinegar to the mayonnaise.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Refrigerate.
The longer they sit, the better they are.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon until crisp; brown hamburger and onion together. Drain excess grease.
Mix all and bake 1 1/2 hours in a 300° oven.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ribs and spaghetti
directions: Mix and pour over 3 1/2 to 5 pound pre-browned ribs in baking dish.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients well. Grease tube or bundt pan. Add mixture to pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350 degrees. Cool completely and frost.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Spread with cherry pie filling.
Makes 8 servings.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Mix bread crumbs, cracker crumbs and butter and spread half of the mixture in a large shallow pan (a large pie pan works well). Arrange oysters in two layers on the crumbs, add remaining ingredients and top with the rest of the crumbs.
Bake in hot (400°) oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
Great for holiday dinners.

title: spicy beef dip
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in skillet until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender; stir in next 4 ingredients.
Cover, simmer for about 10 minutes.
Spoon off excess fat.
Remove from heat.
Add cheeses, heat and stir until cream cheese is melted and well combined.
Keep warm and serve with cracker.

title: mildred's hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light; add vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder together, add to egg and sugar mixture.
Finally add milk and butter which has been heated to boiling.
Pour into greased and floured 9x13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and peppermint extract.
Gradually add powdered sugar; knead until no longer sticky.
Divide into portions.
Knead in food colors of your choice.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Roll balls in powdered sugar.
Flatten balls with a fork.
Let dry at room temperature.
Store loosely covered in refrigerator.
Great gift item and fun for kids!

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix together and form into 1-inch balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate bits over low heat and keep it over heat.
Dip balls on a fork.
Put on wax paper.
Keep in tin in the refrigerator.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves about 8.

title: pineapple congealed salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve sugar in pineapple syrup over low heat; add gelatin.
Stir and let cool slightly. Add pineapple and cheese.
Let cool and add whipped cream.

title: curry chicken
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces, taking off most of fat.
Add all seasonings and onion.
Mix with hand and let sit for 15 minutes. Add oil to pot and when hot, add chicken and 3 cups of water. Cover and let cook on medium for 30 minutes.
Good with rice.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and use as vegetable dip.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Bring oleo and water to boil, take off heat and add flour. Mix with spoon until smooth and let cool.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and beat well after each with a spoon.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan evenly.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375° and cool.

title: shrimp supreme casserole
directions: Shell and clean shrimp, wash, dry well, and set aside.
In 2 tablespoons butter, saute onions, mushrooms and shrimp for 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and paprika, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine cream and flour, make a smooth paste.
Stir flour mixture into shrimp mixture, bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Add rice and mix.
Put into a large casserole. Melt remaining butter, toss with crumbs, sprinkle over casserole. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: johnny marette
directions: Fry pork and onions in shortening.
Stir constantly.
Boil egg noodles in salt water; drain.
Add to pork and onion mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Turn into baking dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in moderate oven for about an hour.

title: you name it!!
directions: Mix crackers, sugar and pecans. Fold in egg whites, beaten stiff with the cream of tartar, into the cracker mixture.
Place in buttered 9 x 15-inch baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: homemade potpourri
directions: Combine all ingredients in a tea kettle or saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer as long as desired.
Check often and add water as needed.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: *"Medium" is hot enough; if you are real brave get a jar of "hot" but don't forget the gallon of water you will need to wash it down.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Add to banana mixture alternately with buttermilk, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Add nuts; mix.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: cold chicken salad
directions: Mix well.
Right before serving, add 1 1/2 cups Grape-Nuts.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Wash and drain berries.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the sugar. Pour into heavy saucepan and bring to a full boil.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring with a wooden spoon.
Stir gently.
Add the other 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Stir and bring to a boil again; boil for 15 minutes more.
Pour into bowl and let stand 24 hours.
Stir occasionally during the 24 hours.
At the end of the time period, spoon into small jars and cover with paraffin.

title: cucumber yum-yum salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups of boiling water.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Put in large, rectangular dish. Keep refrigerated.

title: campbell's 15 minute chicken and rice dinner
directions: Heat oil in a skillet; add chicken.
Cook until browned. Remove chicken.
Add soup, water, paprika and pepper; heat to a boil.
Stir in rice and broccoli; top with chicken.
Season chicken with additional paprika and pepper.
Cover; cook over low heat 5 minutes or until done.
Serves 4.

title: texas caviar dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in the order stated. Enjoy!

title: hodgepodge salad
directions: After all vegetables are prepared and meat and cheese cut, line bowl with fresh, cleaned cabbage leaves.
Add all ingredients.
Cover with creamy buttermilk salad dressing or whatever you prefer.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: chicken and parmesan
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat in 2 tablespoons hot oleo, cook mushrooms and carrots until tender and liquid is absorbed, stirring occasionally.
Stir in half and half, remaining oleo, pepper and nutmeg.
Heat to simmering; gradually stir in cheese and add peas and chicken.
Heat through.
Meanwhile, cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
In a large serving bowl, gently toss hot noodles with chicken mixture.
Serve immediately with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 5 servings.

title: beef goulash
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package; drain. Brown ground beef along with onion, green pepper, garlic, salt and pepper. Drain off as much fat as possible from meat. Add the cooked meat mixture to the cooked pasta. Add the tomato soup and both cans of chopped tomatoes. (Do not drain the chopped tomatoes.) Mix ingredients together. Heat on low on top of stove until good and hot. Before serving, sprinkle cheese on top. Makes 4 generous servings. Goes well with a salad and hot corn bread.

title: monkey bread
directions: Open tubes, separate biscuits and cut each one in quarters. Mix cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar together.
Roll biscuit pieces in mixture.
Spray a Bundt pan with nonstick oil.
Melt the stick of butter.
Dump biscuits into Bundt pan.
Pour the cup of sugar over top of biscuits and the melted butter over sugar.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes, then turn onto plate. Servings pull apart (don't cut with knife).

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter and cook, stirring, until glossy.
Very good for icing for plain cake layers or cupcakes.

title: bean dish
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, remove bacon. To bacon fat add; brown sugar, salt, vinegar, dry mustard, garlic powder and onions. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Fold in chopped apples.
You can add a cup of nuts, coconut or raisins. Bake in 14 x 10 x 2-inch pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: olive-cheese ball
directions: Blend cheeses and butter.
Stir in olives and chives.
Chill for easier handling.
Form into ball on serving plate.
Chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, sprinkle nuts over ball.
Trim with parsley, if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: tuna mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; place over hot water and stir until dissolved.
Combine tuna, lemon juice, mayonnaise and onion in small mixer bowl; beat until smooth.
Stir in dissolved gelatin, sour cream and capers.
Spoon into 3-cup mold and chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Unmold and garnish with thinly sliced cucumbers and cherry tomatoes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Melt the chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Add the marshmallows and peanuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: weekend chowder
directions: In a saucepan, stir cream of chicken soup.
Gradually stir in broth and water (slowly or mixture will be lumpy).
Add potatoes. Boil 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Makes about 8 1/2 cups or 6 servings.
Recipe may be doubled.
Excellent way to use up leftover odds and ends of frozen vegetables.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain, then mash artichoke hearts with a fork.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Before serving, top with red pepper.
Serve with crackers or Melba rounds.
Yield: 1 cup.

title: cajun sauce piquant
directions: In large Dutch oven, make roux with flour and cooking oil. Cook roux until light brown. Add onions, green peppers, celery and garlic. Saute for 5 to 10 minutes until tender. Using a blender, blend tomatoes with green chili peppers until smooth. Add blended mixture, tomato sauce, chicken broth, salt, black pepper and red pepper to Dutch oven. Simmer uncovered for 45 to 60 minutes or until thick. Stir in fish pieces and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes. Season to taste. Serve over rice.

title: seafood alfredo
directions: In a medium saucepan, saute onion and bell pepper in butter until onions are clear.
Add alfredo mix and prepare according to package directions, but reduce liquid by 1/2 cup.
Season seafood to taste.
Add to alfredo mixture when almost done and cover and simmer on low heat for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: swiss anita
directions: Combine 1/2 cup juice from tomatoes, A.1. sauce and cornstarch.
Use a pan approximately 10 x 14 x 2. Place a large sheet of heavy-duty aluminum foil in pan to form a leaf proof bag. Spread center with butter.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Partially bake pie shell about 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and lower temperature to 325°.
In a mixing bowl, combine bacon, mushrooms, cheese, onion, flour, salt and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Spoon into pie shell.
Beat together eggs and milk.
Pour over bacon mixture.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 50 to 60 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: creme au chocolate de zulma
directions: Put chocolate and coffee into an enamel saucepan.
Set over heat and stir until completely smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in egg yolks and the milk.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until the mixture begins to thicken.
Add the vanilla, continuing to stir until a simmer is almost reached.
Set aside.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix well; chill and roll.
Cut with favorite cookie cutters. Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Frost and decorate as desired.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook rigatoni as directed on package; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Toss with rigatoni.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours, but no longer than 24 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: dill toasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove crusts from bread.
Stack slices of bread and cut diagonally into triangles.
Combine melted butter, oil and dill in a bowl.
Brush triangles on both sides with the mixture and arrange on baking sheets.
Bake just until golden, about 10 minutes.
Remove.
The toasts can be made 5 to 6 hours ahead.
Leave at cool room temperature, covered loosely with foil.

title: honey glaze
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Blend well.

title: enchiladas
directions: Saute the onion and green pepper in skillet until tender.
Add tomato sauce, Tabasco sauce and chili powder.
Simmer 30 minutes. Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until ground beef is crumbly.
Drain.
Place 2 to 4 tablespoons of meat and equal amount of shredded cheese in center of each tortilla.
Roll up to enclose filling, securing with wooden picks.
Pour 1/2 cup of tomato sauce mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange tortillas in dish; cover with remaining sauce . Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave on Medium for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top with additional cheese.

title: pesto
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender, using the low chopping speed.
Stop every few seconds and scrape sides of blender down so that everything is evenly mixed and blended to a smooth consistency.
The sauce can be stored in a jar in the refrigerator for several weeks.
After it is placed in the jar, add more oil to cover top of sauce.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Sift flour,
soda,
cinnamon,
sugar and salt together, then add
yams,	cooking
oil,
water, eggs, pecans and dates. Grease and
flour 2 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Fill each one half full and bake
hour
Time will vary; may not take the entire hour.
Remove from cans immediately.

title: spiced tea
directions: Steep the 5 tablespoons tea in 2 cups of the boiling water for 4 minutes.
Add the remainder of boiling water to the sugar and spices (best put in spice bag).
Stir until dissolved.
Add the remaining ingredients and bring to a simmer; do not boil.
Keeps well in the refrigerator.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream sugars, vanilla, oil and eggs.
Add flour and other dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes, until edges are light brown.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Place blueberries in buttered 1 1/4-quart shallow baking dish. Combine sugar, orange peel, mace and cardamom.
Sprinkle sugar mixture and pie crust mix in alternate layers over blueberries. Continue until all is used.
Dot with butter.
Drizzle lemon juice and vanilla over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: julie's chili-o salad
directions: Prepare ahead 24 hours.
Cook your favorite macaroni, drain and rinse in cold water.
Mix together the Chili-O mix, ketchup, vinegar and mayonnaise; stir into macaroni.
Add celery and beans; mix.
Double for large bowl.

title: one bowl cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: willia's sprinkle nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease & flour a 10-inch tube pan. In a large bowl, combine cake mix, sour cream & sugar. Add oil, water, and eggs. On low speed, beat the mixture 30 seconds until moistened. On medium speed, beat for 2 minutes. Stir in nuts and sprinkles; pour into prepared pan. Bake in oven for 60 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Drain meat.
Add beans, seasoning package and tomato juice.
Mix well and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Melt stick of butter and saute onion in frying pan, then brown cut up chicken breasts.
In another pot, mix rest of ingredients and simmer until melted.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth, then drain.
Mix all together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peach gelatin pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water, salt, lemon juice.
Add sugar to peeled and sliced peaches.
Combine whipping cream with cooled gelatin mixture and add peaches.
Fill pie crusts and refrigerate.

title: one-bowl chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan or have ready 12 to 18 cupcake liners in cupcake pan.

Do not mix until all ingredients are in the bowl. Beat all ingredients until smooth with mixer. Pour into prepared pan or cupcake liners (1/2 full). Bake at 350° about 40 minutes for cake or 15 to 20 minutes for cupcakes. The top gets sticky as it cools.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to Crisco mixture. Add chips and mix well. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: easy chicken lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix milk and soup.
Spread 1/2 cup of the soup mixture in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Top with 4 uncooked noodles.
Mix chicken, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, cottage cheese and spinach.
Spread half of the chicken mixture over noodles in dish; top with 1/2 cup of the soup mixture.
Repeat with 4 uncooked noodles, remaining chicken mixture and 1/2 cup of the soup mixture.
Top with remaining uncooked noodles and soup mixture.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake about 1 hour or until noodles are tender.
Uncover and let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Yields 8 servings.

title: molded salad
directions: In a very large bowl, dissolve gelatin in water (hot).
Stir in cold water.
Chill until thickened but not set (45 minutes). Add mayonnaise and blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Spoon into a 12-cup mold.
Chill.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Combine biscuit mix and water, stirring with fork until blended.
Press mixture in bottom of lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes.

title: tex-mex cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in 6 slices and cook 10 minutes or until tender but crisp.
Pour in buttered 2-quart dish.
Saute onion, green pepper, sugar and butter.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper. Pour over cabbage and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated through.
Can cut hot dogs and put on top.

title: kentucky pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together; add oil and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and beat well.
Add pumpkin and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes, then turn out on rack.

title: chicken tahitian
directions: In a saucepan, melt the oleo; stir in the soup mix and cornstarch.
Add pineapple and lemon or lime juice.
Arrange chicken and pineapple in a pan.
Pour onion mix over and bake until tender in 350° oven.

title: pecan-coconut pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Add margarine, pecans, coconut and salt.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch glass pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: saltless seasoning salt
directions: Mix together and store in a closed container in a dry place. This is delicious on many foods...salads, meats, vegetables (cooked or raw).

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco; add baking powder and milk, then yeast mixture.
Store in refrigerator
in covered bowl; use as needed.
Roll out and make into rolls 30 minutes before baking.
Let rise in a warm place.

title: pineapple marshmallow salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and place in double boiler.
Beat sugar, flour and eggs together, then add to hot pineapple juice and continue cooking until thick.
While this cools, cut pineapple, oranges and marshmallows into small pieces.
Whip the 1/2 cup cream and fold into the pudding mixture.
Pour this over the fruit and marshmallows; add nuts.
Stir all together and let stand before serving.

title: hamburgers and brown gravy
directions: *The items are to be used accordingly to your taste.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O
in
water.
Add pineapple, blueberries and chill.
Mix cream
cheese,	sour cream, powdered sugar and pecans. Spread on top of Jell-O.
Chill.

title: beer batter fried shrimp
directions: Open the can of mackerel and drain off the fluid.
Put the fish sections in a bowl.
Gently open up the middle of the fish sections and remove the spiny bones.
Dispose of the fish bones.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in a saucepan.
Boil and cook for 1 minute.
Remove and stir in peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Beat until it loses its gloss.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper; cool 10 minutes.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon in heavy skillet until brown.
Remove bacon from skillet.
Add okra to bacon drippings.
Fry until no longer slimy. Add bell pepper, onion, salt and pepper.
Fry until onion is clear.
Add tomatoes and sugar.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: upside-down chili pie
directions: Saute meat and onion in shortening.
Add kidney beans, chili powder, salt, Worcestershire sauce and tomatoes.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish and top with cornmeal batter made by mixing remaining ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: cream tuna on toast
directions: Blend soup and milk in saucepan until smooth.
Add tuna and heat thoroughly.
While heating prepare 8 slices toast.
Spoon mixture on toast and enjoy!

title: caesar salad and dressing
directions: Place all ingredients (except Parmesan, lettuce and croutons) in a blender.
Blend until creamy.
Pour over lettuce which you've broken into small pieces.
Toss with Parmesan cheese.
Toss with croutons.
Top with additional fresh ground pepper (to taste). Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Combine soups, chiles, spices, Tabasco sauce and broth in large pan and heat until warm.
Layer in large baking dish, beginning with layer of chips, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 sauce and 1/2 cheese and repeat layers.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: austin and jennie's favorite breakfast
directions: Pour cereal into bowl; pour milk over cereal.
Quick, easy and ready to eat in 15 seconds.

title: christmas fruit punch
directions: Make simple syrup of sugar and water.
Put spices in a bag, tied at the top.
Add bag of spices to syrup mixture; let stand for several hours.
Remove spice bag.
Combine syrup with all the juices.
Serve.

title: chocolate zucchini nut bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder together.
Add to zucchini mixture, blending well.
Stir in chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Grease and flour lightly two 5 x 9 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Pour batter into pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until bread tests done.

title: lattice top for chicken bake
directions: Place vegetables in a greased 8 x 12-inch dish.
Mix soup, milk and 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Put cubed chicken over vegetables.
Cover with soup mixture, then with onions.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Heat first 2 ingredients on low heat until mixture bubbles or microwave 2 minutes, stir and microwave 1 minute more.
Cool.
Add eggs one at a time, while beating with electric mixer.
Fold in flour, salt and baking powder and mix well.
Add coconut, nut meats and vanilla.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt oleo in a 13 x 9-inch pan in oven.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over melted oleo.
Pour condensed milk over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients. Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° (325° for glass pans).
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.
Makes 24 bars.

title: boneless barbecue pork loin
directions: Cook roast on grill on medium-slow to slow for 2 hours with a pan of water beside roast.
Internal temperature of roast should be 170° when done, or bake in oven at 325° for 2 hours.
Baste frequently with sauce.
Serve with sauce when roast is done.

title: barbecue beef(15 minute preparation)
directions: Cut steak into 1/8 to 1/4-inch strips, 1-inch wide.
Put aside.
Cook and stir thin sliced onions in oil in large skillet on medium high heat for 3 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove and keep warm.
Add beef strips (1/2 at a time).
Cook and stir 3 minutes.
Add barbecue sauce and onions.
Heat until hot.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 55 to 60 minutes.
Rub butter around pan.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly, reserving 1 cup.
Pat remaining mixture lightly into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: southwest meatballs
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, heat 1 tablespoon oil. Add onion and chili powder. Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until onion is tender and well coated with powder. Remove from heat. Let cool. Spoon onion into large bowl. Wipe out skillet. Add beef, bread crumbs, egg and salt to onion in bowl. Using hand or wooden spoon, blend well. Shape into 1-inch balls. To skillet, add remaining 2 tablespoons oil. Heat over medium-high heat. Add meatballs. Cook about 12 minutes until browned on all sides and cooked through. Stir in taco sauce and tomatoes. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to low. Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: pastry(for eight 8-inch two crust pies)
directions: Mix flour and shortening 1 minute on low speed.
Add remaining ingredients slowly and mix for 40 seconds on low speed.
Mix with minimum handling to form a dough.
Scale 5 ounces for bottom crust and 4 ounces for top crust.
Let stand 10 minutes in refrigerator before rolling.
Bake pie shell 8 to 10 minutes at 450°.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients, except Kisses.
Roll into little balls (optional: roll cookie balls in sugar).
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Place Kisses on top.
Bake an additional 2 minutes. Cool.

title: pecan logs
directions: Melt marshmallows and condensed milk in top of double boiler. Mix with other ingredients.
Roll in crushed nuts.
Makes 2 long pecan rolls or several small ones.

title: cream puffs
directions: Add shortening to boiling water.
Bring to boil.
Add flour; stir vigorously until ball forms.
Cool slightly and add unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Mixture will be stiff.
Drop by spoonful. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes.
(See Custard Filling for stuffing.)

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and nuts and spread in 13 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Whip 2 packages Dream Whip with 3/4 cup milk.
Add 8 ounces cream cheese and 1 pound powdered sugar.
Pour on cold crust.
Spread cherry pie filling over top.

title: punch bowl salad
directions: In a punch bowl, layer, starting with cake, pudding, fruit and Cool Whip.
Make approximately 3 layers of the sequence.
End with Cool Whip and chill.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: In
a
large bowl, combine flour, soda, cinnamon, salt, brown sugar
and granulated sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add rest of ingredients and stir until well combined.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls
on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 12 minutes, until lightly browned.	Makes 48 cookies.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together hamburg, onion, soup, oatmeal and eggs.
Shape into balls; place on cookie sheet and brown in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: sausage and egg souffle
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in a covered bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Excellent for brunch. Serves 6 to 8.

title: gumbo soup(one of my favorites)
directions: Cook soup bone and chuck meats until tender; add mixed vegetables, macaroni, onion and corn until tender.
Add tomatoes and okra.
Season.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter in heavy bottomed saucepan. Stir over low heat until cheese is soft, butter is melted, and the mix is blended.
Add the powdered sugar and stir until well combined.
Add your choice of food coloring and flavoring; 2 or 3 different choices of color can be used by dividing the mix.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on a sheet of waxed paper.
Press with fork.
Let stand, uncovered, 4 hours, or overnight, until mints dry and firm.
Inside will be creamy.

title: creamy cabbage soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot butter, cook cabbage and onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in ham.
Stir in soup and milk until smooth.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: stew
directions: I layer these items in my slow cooker.
Mix the soup with 1/2 can of water and pour over the top.
Cook on low all day.

title: easy company chicken breasts
directions: Mix crumbs with other ingredients, except chicken and butter. Pound chicken breast halves until quite thin.
Melt oleo and coat chicken breasts thoroughly.
Let stand for 5 minutes only.
Coat chicken with mix.
Place in foil covered pan sprayed with Pam. Cover with foil or Saran if refrigerated until baking.
Be sure the chicken is at room temperature before baking.
If used promptly, place in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes only.
It will depend upon the thickness.
It is important not to allow them to dry out.
May be served with mustard sauce.

title: german potato salad
directions: Slice potatoes in bowl.
Fry bacon and drain, set aside. Saute onion and celery in bacon grease.
Pour off drippings leaving 1 Tbsp. in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients, except bacon and parsley.
Bring to boil for 1/2 minute to 1 minute. Pour over potatoes and toss.
Add bacon and parsley.
Let stand 3 minutes.

title: banana lumpia
directions: Peel banana and slice it in half (lengthwise).
Wrap it with lumpia wrapper and fry it until brown.

title: texas chocolate cake
directions: Bring to a boil the butter, water and cocoa.
Add all at once to mixture of first 6 ingredients.
Mix well and pour in greased, oblong pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger and bean pot
directions: Crumble and fry hamburger and onion in skillet until hamburger is slightly brown and onion is clear; drain off all fat.
Place pork and beans in large deep baking dish.
Mix in molasses, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
If pork and beans are too dry, may need to add 1/4 cup water.
Mix 3/4 of hamburger and onion with pork and bean mixture.
Place remainder of hamburger on top.
Bake in microwave for 15 minutes on High, covered with glass lid or double plastic wrap.
Serve hot.
This goes well on cold winter evenings with a bowl of cole slaw and rolls.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes in electric mixer.
Add the sugar, eggs, vanilla, butter, cinnamon, nutmeg, and milk to the potatoes.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Combine brown sugar, chopped nuts, flour, and 1/3 cup butter.
Crumble mixture on top of potatoes. Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: white brownies
directions: Melt margarine in large mixing bowl in microwave.
Add cake mix and eggs.
Mix well by spoon.
Add anything to this such as chocolate chips, walnuts, sprinkles or mini M&M's.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until it starts to turn light brown. Cool before you cut or it will get heavy.

title: basic "7" muffins
directions: Mix and sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Combine milk and egg, add to flour mixture.
Mix only enough to dampen flour.
Fold in oat flakes.

title: cocoa walnut fudge
directions: Blend sugar, cocoa and cream of tartar.
Slowly stir in milk until sugar is dissolved.
Do not stir the mixture after it begins to boil.
Cover for the first 5 minutes of boiling, then uncover and boil until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Drop in butter, but do not stir.
When fudge has cooled down some, add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch dish.

title: town farm potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, sweet red pepper, carrots and celery. Pour on the dressing and mix.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add soda, salt and vanilla, then beat in flour.
Roll thin; cut with cutters.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Add beaten egg whites on top of cookies, then sprinkle with sprinkles and nuts. Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: brownie pudding cake
directions: Mix together the sugar, brown sugar and cocoa.
Sprinkle this over cake in pan.
Pour 1 cup of boiling water on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican appetizer
directions: Mix all but tortillas and correct seasoning.
Spread on tortillas and roll like you are making a jelly roll.
Place the seam down on your pan.
Cut into crosswise slices.
Serve with bowl of picante sauce for dipping.

title: ham and broccoli chowder
directions: Cook broccoli in water with bouillon.
Add ham and cheese. Mix flour, milk and pepper in blender.
Add to broccoli slowly. Cook over low heat until thickened.

title: crispy-chewy molasses cookies
directions: Melt butter; cool to room temperature.
Combine butter, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and egg in a large mixing bowl; beat well at medium speed of mixer.
Combine water and soda in small bowl, stirring until soda dissolves.
Add soda mixture to creamed mixture, beating well.
Stir in molasses and flour.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls 3 inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Cool cookies completely on wire racks. Makes 8 dozen.

title: almond bark
directions: Melt almond bark in the microwave for 1 minute. Add almonds; mix well until well coated. Spread in butter pan. Chill until set. Break into pieces.

title: southern oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray large baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large shallow bowl, combine buttermilk and red pepper sauce.
On sheet of wax paper, combine cornflake crumbs, flour, salt and black pepper. Dip chicken pieces in buttermilk mixture.
Dredge, coating completely, with cornflake mixture. Arrange chicken on prepared baking sheet; drizzle evenly with oil.
Bake 30 minutes. Turn pieces over and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until cooked thoroughly.

title: frozen fruit slush
directions: Mix and freeze.
Set out 2 hours ahead of time to let thaw. Serve in punch bowl with orange and lemon slices.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Put
crackers
in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the ice
cream	and
the pudding together, then add the milk. Mix well.
Spread over the crumbs in the pan.
Next spread the Cool Whip on
top.
Sprinkle
with cracker crumbs.
Put in the freezer and cut when ready to serve.

title: chicken a la noel
directions: Cook chickens about 15 to 20 minutes (turn halfway through). Brown chickens in wok (6 minutes).
Put back in sauce and simmer a while longer.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain well.
Add green peppers, onion, cheese, soup, milk and mayo.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325 degrees.

title: double caramel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (8-inch) cake pans. Cream sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Stir in egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and soda.
Mix milk and vanilla.
Add only dry ingredients and milk alternately to creamed mixture, beating gently after each addition.
Combine beaten egg whites with salt and cream of tartar until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into flour mixture. Spread batter in pans.
Bake 25 minutes or until cake tester inserted in centers comes out clean.
Frost with Caramel Frosting and garnish with Chocolate Curls.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: frozen cheese with peach or berry sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except fruit in blender container until smooth.
Turn into refrigerator tray and freeze at coldest point until firm around edges.
Stir with spoon until smooth.
Freeze until firm.
Serve in squares with a fruit sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna according to directions and drain.
Prepare spinach according to directions; drain.
Place enough spaghetti sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan to cover.
Arrange one layer of lasagna in parallel strips on top of sauce.
Top lasagna with cooked spinach.
Arrange second layer of lasagna in parallel strips and top with a layer of sauce.
Next add cottage cheese mixed with egg white, then layer slices of Mozzarella cheese on top of cottage cheese mixture.
Add layer of lasagna and top with sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix well and store in refrigerator until serving time.
Use fresh fruit for this dip.

title: boiled custard
directions: Put pan of milk in pan of water and heat.
Beat eggs and add sugar.
Mix about 2 cups of warm milk into egg mixture, then add it all to heated milk.
When cool, add vanilla and strain.

title: cream cheese and crab dip
directions: Place cream cheese on flat plate.
Cover with cocktail sauce. Put portion of crab meat on top, then use your favorite crackers (Hi Ho, Triscuits or sesame flavored crackers) on the side.

title: sweet n' sour cabbage and veal soup(old weight watchers recipe)
directions: Brown veal or turkey, drain if necessary.
Bring to boil tomato juice plus 3/4 can of water.
Add bouillon, cabbage, celery, parsley and meat.
Simmer until cabbage is tender (about 1/2 hour). Add vinegar and serve.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: crazy crust apple pie
directions: In small mixer bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, egg, Crisco and water; blend well.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into a 9-inch pie pan.
Combine pie filling, lemon juice and spice.
Pour into center of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes, until crust is golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and form into a ball. Roll in pecans. Refrigerate before serving. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: vegetable medley
directions: In large skillet, saute zucchini, peas, celery and onion in butter for 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Cover pan part of the cooking time.
Stir in salt, oregano and garlic salt.

title: broccoli and grape salad
directions: Step 1:
In a mixing bowl, stir together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.

title: rolled stuffed eggplant
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Lightly oil 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Combine all ingredients, save for eggplant and olive oil. Brush both sides of eggplant slices with oil. Cook in skillet until golden, about 5 minutes on each side. Remove to platter. Spread mound of cheese mixture at the base of each eggplant slice, then roll it up. Arrange rolls seam side down in the baking dish. Cover dish and bake until heated through and cheese is melted, about 20 minutes. Remove rolls to warmed plates. Serve with fresh tomato sauce.

title: german chocolate frosting
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and stir over medium heat until thick (approximately 12 minutes).
Let cool.
Add coconut and chopped pecans.

title: southern banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix, egg yolks and milk in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil. Remove from heat,
Cover surface of hot pudding with wax paper or plastic wrap.
Cool.

title: egg custard
directions: Heat ingredients until butter melts. Pour into a pie crust that is partially done. Put into oven at 400° and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Add yeast to water.
Mix other ingredients together.
Add yeast.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs, then add pineapple, sugar, vanilla and nuts. Combine baking soda, salt and flour into egg mixture.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
A cream cheese frosting can be used or cake can be eaten plain.
This cake is very moist.

title: easy clam chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook in slow cooker for 6 hours on low.
Serve with crackers.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in large pan.
Heat to boiling; turn off heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips together over low heat.
Spread over Rice Krispies mixture.
Refrigerate until solid; cut into squares.

title: "down the bay" salad
directions: Mix vegetables and cheese.
Add chopped eggs.
Toss with enough mayonnaise to coat all ingredients.
(Adjust amount of ingredients to suit individual taste.)

title: lemon pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add egg yolks, milk, juice and grated rind.
Beat with eggbeater.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased baking dish set in a pan of hot water for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split pizza
directions: Bake brownie mix in a pizza pan, adding 1 extra egg.
Cool completely.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large bowl and mix.
Pour dressing over salad.
Mix in crushed Doritos before serving.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Heat oil and garlic in skillet until lightly browned.
Stir in slowly, water, parsley and oregano; add slowly, clams and juice. Cook until clams are heated through.
Serve hot on cooked spaghetti or macaroni.

title: world famous shish kabob marinade
directions: Put beef cubes in marinade and refrigerate overnight. Leftover marinade can be frozen or stored in refrigerator for one week.
Tastes great when used with chicken kabobs, too!

title: ham it up crescent snacks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 4 long rectangles. Firmly press diagonal perforation to seal.
Place ham slices on rectangles.
Spread ham slices with mustard.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Starting at short side, roll up each rectangle.
Press edges to seal.
Coat rolls with sesame seed.
Cut each of the 4 rolls into 5 slices, forming 20 slices.
Place each slice, cut side down, on an ungreased 12 x 15-inch rectangle baking dish. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Serves 8.

title: egg custard pie(makes one 9-inch pie)
directions: Melt butter.
Beat eggs with fork and add to milk.
Combine with butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Beat eggs well; mix all the ingredients into the eggs.
Pour in well-greased pan, 9 x 13-inch. Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Allow to cool before removing from pan.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Toss cheese and flour.
Add half and half, eggs, ham and seasonings; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: seven pound fudge(this fudge recipe is scrumptious.)
directions: Cook, over low heat, the milk and syrup, and stir often to keep from scorching.
Cook approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Arrange pecans on a buttered cookie sheet, usually 5 per turtle so it looks like a turtle with four legs and a head.
Drop the mixture by teaspoon over each pecan pile.

title: cucumber dressing
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, salt, sour cream and cucumber.
Chill. Makes 2 1/2 cups dressing.
A salad dressing of cucumbers and sour cream or yogurt is especially designed to serve over sliced tomatoes or sliced beets.

title: herbal mayonnaise
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend for 1 minute.
Yields 1 cup.

title: potato soup
directions: Fry bacon crisp; drain.
Crumble.
Add potato to bacon grease; brown.
Add soup mix, water and tomato juice.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add peas and bacon.

title: drunken figs
directions: Coffee:
Prepare strong black coffee, allow to cool and freeze in ice cube tray.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press 1/2-inch thick in square pan.
Cut in pieces.
Chill before serving.

title: date bread
directions: Pour water and soda over raisins and dates and let set.
Mix all and pour into greased pans.
Makes 2 large loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Combine with other ingredients except the nuts.
Mix well and form into ball or log. Place on waxed paper and chill.
Roll in pecans.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate.

title: old fashioned pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients, then add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: apple pie in a bag
directions: Mix apples, sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Pile in unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with lemon juice.

title: roasted garlic soup
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut off top 1/4-inch of each garlic head.
Place heads in small shallow baking dish.
Drizzle oil over and bake until golden, about 1 hour.
Cool slightly.
Squeeze garlic cloves between fingers to remove skin.
Chop garlic.
Melt butter in heavy pan over medium heat.
Add garlic, leeks and onion; saute until soft, about 8 minutes.
Reduce heat to low. Add flour and cook 10 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in broth and sherry.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Puree soup in blender.
Return to pan.
Add cream and simmer 10 minutes.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve garnished with chives.
Serves 4.
Freezes well.

title: easy nut cups
directions: Melt chips and oil in top of double boiler. Remove from heat. Add peanuts. Cool slightly. Drop by teaspoon into candy cups. Refrigerate.

title: white trash
directions: In pan melt 3 teaspoons of oil and chocolate together over low heat.
Place dry mixtures in a bowl and pour chocolate-oil mixture over it.
Mix.
Layer mixture over sheets of waxed paper until hard.
Store in airtight container.

title: never fail pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix softened butter, oil and sugar well. Add eggs, beaten in one at a time.
Add flour, baking powder and milk alternately, beating well after each addition.
Add flavorings.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: citrus punch
directions: Mix each can according to directions on can.
Keep refrigerated until ready to use.
Pour into punch bowl and add ginger ale.
Add sliced limes, lemons and oranges.

title: hot punch
directions: Pour first 3 ingredients in percolator.
Place remaining ingredients in percolator basket and perk through cycle.
Serves approximately 7 cups.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by tablespoons on cookie sheet. Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 45 minutes.
For a milder sauce, omit the cayenne pepper.

title: eye of the round roast with vegetables
directions: Rub Gravy Master into all sides of roast.
Sprinkle garlic powder over complete surface of roast.
Place cut up vegetables into 7 x 11-inch pan.
Season with salt, pepper and parsley.
Place meat in center of pan, fat side up.
Cover with foil.
Insert a meat thermometer through the foil into thickest part of the roast. With cooking fork, pierce the foil 3 to 4 times.
Roast at 400° until desired doneness is reached.
Rare will take about 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: party dip
directions: Mix contents of Ranch party dip and sour cream together. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: baked tuna and macaroni with mushroom sauce
directions: Place macaroni in 5 quarts boiling salted water. Combine soups and milk; blend to a smooth cream while heating, then season. Place drained macaroni in greased casserole; add chunks of tuna and sauce. Top with crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake in 450° oven until top is lightly brown. Serves 6.

title: homemade finger paint
directions: Mix flour with salt.
Add cold water.
Stir until smooth. Gradually add this mixture to boiling water.
Boil until smooth and thick.
Add food coloring, then stir until smooth.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add eggs, then milk alternately with dry ingredients.
May be dropped by teaspoon or rolled out.
Bake at 300° until lightly brown.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except cucumbers and mix well.
Stir in cucumbers.
Serve with chips or vegetables.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Cook and stir chicken and onion in hot butter in large skillet until chicken is lightly browned.
Add garlic and cook 30 seconds. Add spinach, broth and water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, stirring 3 minutes.
Stir in rice and cheese.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Makes 3 servings.

title: four-layer dessert
directions: Mix crust ingredients together and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, syrup and butter.
Add pecans and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crusts and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: egg custard
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg.
Beat 3 egg yolks and add to dry ingredients.
Beat well; add milk.
Stir in butter. Pour in crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Beat egg whites and top them on pie.

title: egg rolls
directions: In wok or skillet, heat 1/4 cup oil; add onion and carrots. Cook for 5 minutes; meat also, if used in recipe.
Add all other ingredients; simmer until tender and add cornstarch.
Wrap and fry in oil until crisp on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with hot or mild Chinese mustard and sweet and sour sauce.

title: apple chicken casserole
directions: Saute green pepper in margarine; reduce heat.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually add milk, cook until thickened.
Add 1 cup cheese and stir until melted.
Stir in chopped apples, rice and chicken.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese; garnish with apple slices and almonds, if desired.
Continue baking until cheese is completely melted.

title: classic belgian waffles
directions: Preheat the waffle iron according to the manufacturer's instructions. In 1 medium bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Set aside. In a second bowl, use the wooden spoon to beat together the egg yolks and sugar until sugar is completely dissolved and eggs have turned
a pale yellow. Add the vanilla extract, melted butter and milk
to the eggs and whisk to combine. Combine the egg-milk mixture with the flour mixture and whisk just until blended. Do not overmix. In third bowl, beat

the egg whites with an electric mixer until soft peaks form, about 1 minute. Using the rubber spatula, gently fold the egg whites into the waffle batter. Do not overmix! Coat the waffle iron with nonstick cooking spray and pour enough batter in iron to just cover waffle grid. Close and cook as per manufacturer's instructions until golden brown, about 2 to 3 minutes. Serve immediately with assorted toppings. Strawberries, blueberries, whipped cream, maple syrup, powdered sugar and banana are all excellent with these waffles.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Stir together strawberries and 1/4 cup sugar, set aside.
For shortcake, thoroughly stir together flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in the 1/2 cup butter or margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine beaten egg and milk; add all at once to dry ingredients and stir just to moisten. Spread dough in a greased 8 x 1 1/2 inch round baking pan, building up edges slightly.
Bake in a 450° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool in pan, 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Split in 2 layers; lift top off carefully.
If desired, spread bottom layer with softened butter.
Whip cream with 2 tablespoon sugar just to soft peaks. Spoon berries and whipped cream between layers and over top.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: feta-cini with artichokes(healthy)
directions: Saute onion, garlic and green pepper in oil until softened. Add tomatoes and cook 4 minutes. Toss remaining ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all in blender at high speed.
Blend for 5 minutes. Butter pie plate.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 300° to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except Lipton soup mix.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle the dry soup mix over top of chicken.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake approximately 2 hours at 300° to 350°.
May need to add more water as it cooks.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute together ground beef and onion.
Add next 6 ingredients. Cut tortillas into fourths or halves.
Line the bottom of a greased casserole pan with layer of sauce, then a layer of tortillas, then sauce, then tortillas, until you have used all tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 1 large or 2 small casseroles.
Let set in the refrigerator overnight before baking.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Use food processor to grate Cheddar cheese.
Chop Blue cheese and cream cheese.
Add to food processor along with butter, Worcestershire
and spices.
Process until smooth.
Chill mixture for 3 hours; wrap in plastic wrap.
Shape into a large ball or two 3-inch balls.
Roll in chopped pecans to coat.
Wrap in plastic wrap and place in Ziploc bag.
Keep refrigerated.
May be frozen. If frozen, thaw at room temperature for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix as pie dough.
Spread over mixture.
Bake until bubbly until light brown at 350°.

title: company muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, oat bran, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Stir in sugar. Add carrots, apples, raisins and nuts.
Stir well.
Make a well in the center.
Add oil, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Stir just until moistened.
Use a 1/4 cup measure to scoop muffin mixture into greased tins.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until nicely browned. Makes 18 muffins.

title: spinach torta
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
In a large bowl place spinach, bread (torn into pieces, crust too!), milk and cheese.
Mix together. Place the remaining ingredients in a blender and mix well.
Pour blended portion over mixture in bowl.
Mix evenly.
Pour into greased 8 x 10-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: In large skillet, cook beef until it loses its red color.
Add the next 7 ingredients and stir.
Stir in cooked spaghetti. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover and heat for 15 minutes, until bubbly.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings in half at joint; cut off tips of wings and discard.
Combine chicken and remaining ingredients in a shallow container.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours; turn occasionally. Remove chicken from marinade; place single layer on pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; turn each piece and bake another 15 minutes or until done.

title: sourdough flapjacks from herman
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let mixture foam 1 minute.
Drop on griddle.

title: spinach salad
directions: Assemble all ingredients and serve either salad bar style where everyone can include what they want and add their own dressing when they are ready to eat.
Or keep everything separate in the refrigerator until ready to eat and then toss in a salad bowl with the dressing.
Only fix just enough if tossing because everything will get soggy and will not save very well.

title: crab quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a bowl, combine egg substitute, mayonnaise, flour, thyme and black pepper.
Mix well.
Gently stir in cheese, onion and crabmeat.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean, about 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt butter in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix first 6 ingredients together and pour on top of melted butter.
Spread out evenly.

title: hamburger party stew
directions: Shape ground beef into 4 patties.
Melt shortening in heavy skillet.
Remove from heat.
Spread rice and onion soup mix evenly over bottom of skillet and arrange patties on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Combine mushroom soup with water until smooth and pour over all.
Cover and simmer over medium heat 20 to 30 minutes or until meat patties are cooked through.
Serves 4.

title: 14 day pickles
directions: In large kettle, place 2 gallons washed cucumbers.
Add 1 pint of salt to each gallon of water.
Let stand 1 week.
Pour off water; rinse cucumbers.
Split each cucumber and return to kettle.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 24 hours; pour off water.
Return to kettle; cover with boiling water and alum. Leave 24 hours; pour off water.
Return to kettle; cover with hot vinegar, sugar, celery seed and cinnamon bark.
Pour off and reheat vinegar mixture for next 3 days.
Last day, heat mixture and pour over cucumbers in hot jars and seal.

title: beef or steak marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate any type of steak or beef for at least 8 hours, turning occasionally.
Pierce steak to allow marinate to penetrate meat.
Make sure steak is at least 1/2 covered at all time.
Cook steak as usual.

title: pumpkin pie dessert
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients into custard and pour into large oblong Pyrex pan which has been sprayed generously with Pam.
Then mix butter or margarine into cake mix.
Mix until crumbly.
Spread evenly over custard mix in Pyrex pan.
Sprinkle top with walnuts. Bake in 350° oven for one hour and ten minutes.
Serve with or without whipped cream.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: fresh strawberries with cream dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream in a small bowl.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and liqueur, mixing well.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve with fresh strawberries.
Yields 2 cups.

title: scalloped potatoes with ham
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt and pepper and set aside. Place a layer of sliced potatoes in casserole dish. Add a layer of ham and onion slices. Repeat until used. Pour soup mixture over all. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour. Uncover and add cheese, then sprinkle with paprika for added garnish. Reduce heat to 350° and return to oven for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: german style potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Slice into large bowl.
Add onion cut into small pieces.
Fry bacon until well done.
Pour in vinegar and sugar and salt.
Bring to boil and thicken with flour and water mixture or cornstarch and water mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over potatoes until well mixed.

title: fruit compote
directions: Mix all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: toffee squares
directions: In mixing bowl, cream together butter and brown sugar until light-colored and fluffy.
Add egg yolk and vanilla.
Gradually beat in flour until smooth and blended.
(Dough will be thick.) Spread evenly on 14 x 16-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until crust is golden brown and puffy.
Remove from oven.
Arrange unwrapped chocolate bars evenly over top of crust. Let stand 5 minutes to soften.
Spread chocolate evenly over crust. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cool and cut into squares. Yield: 40 squares.

title: quick pizza sauce
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Use as desired.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Sift flour and dry ingredients together. Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in a 4 to 6-quart microwave-safe utensil. Combine sugar, margarine, syrup and salt in 1-quart glass batter bowl.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes; stir.
Microwave on High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Stir well.

Pour mixture immediately over popcorn, stirring to coat evenly. Microwave on High 2 minutes, stirring midway through cooking. Turn out onto a piece of wax paper or aluminum foil to cool. Break into pieces and store in an airtight container.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In shallow baking pan, thoroughly blend all ingredients except potatoes.
Add potatoes and turn to coat thoroughly.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: fat-free french fries
directions: Cut potatoes into French fries.
Mix egg whites; dip fries in whites and mix well.
On baking sheet, arrange fries and add seasonings.
Bake at 350° turning potatoes on all sides for crispness.
Cook until golden brown.
Tastes great!

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
While cooking, mix stuffing with water and butter per package directions.
Mix broccoli and stuffing.
Place in a buttered baking dish.
Mix soup and milk together and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into pie shells.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain corn and beans.
Mix all together except crackers.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with crackers.
Pour melted butter over that, then sprinkle on almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple-gelatin mixture.
Stir until blended.
Chill until partially set; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into ring mold. Chill until firm.

title: date nut roll
directions: Cook sugar, milk and dates until it reaches the soft ball stage.
Add butter and vanilla; beat until thick.
Add nuts; roll in damp cloth and chill until set.
Slice and eat.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix together melted butter and soda crackers. Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan. Beat egg whites until foamy, then gradually add sugar, salt and cream of tartar as in making a meringue. Spread on top of crackers. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool. Spread lemon pie filling over meringue. If not enough, you may add more filling. Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate until served. Serves 12 to 16.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with milk and sour cream to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: banana bites
directions: Peel the bananas, then slice them into 1-inch pieces.
Cover a cookie sheet with aluminum foil or wax paper.
Crush the peanuts. Mix them with wheat germ and spread the mixture on a dinner plate. Pour the honey into a small bowls.
Dip each banana piece in the honey, then roll it in the nut mixture.
Line the bananas up on the cookie sheet.
Place the cookie sheet in the freezer for 1 or 2 hours.
Eat while still frozen.

title: lentil soup
directions: Cook ground chuck in 6-quart Dutch oven.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Cook over high heat until mixture comes to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours or until lentils are tender.

title: beef brisket
directions: Place brisket in broiler pan or baking dish.
Sprinkle wine or vinegar over brisket.
Sprinkle generously with rest of seasonings except onion.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Remove cover and place in 350° oven for 1 hour to brown.
Remove to baking dish or Dutch oven (something with tight lid).
Slice onion over top of brisket.
Use drippings from browning pan.
Add enough water to make 2 cups of liquid.
Pour over brisket.
Cover tightly and put in 300° oven for 4 hours until tender.
Cool in liquid. Refrigerate overnight.
Remove and dispose of fat that congeals on top.
Slice.
Can freeze at this point or refrigerate.
When ready to serve, heat in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Gravy is thin, but delicious.
Good cold.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place in 9 x 13-inch pan: rice, water and soup mix.
Salt and pepper pork chops and layer over rice.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until pork chops are ready.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix all but ketchup together.
Place in a microwave casserole. Spread ketchup over top of loaf.
Cook on Medium-high for 25 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: chopped turkey diane(quick!)
directions: Mix ground turkey with
1/4 cup of margarine, 2 tablespoons of chopped parsley, 2 teaspoons green of scallions, squeezed bread, salt and pepper either by hand or in food processor.
Shape into 7 to 8 patties.
Melt 1 or 2 tablespoons of margarine in frypan. Fry patties over medium-low heat until browned and meat is just cooked through, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Remove and keep warm. Saute onion; do not brown.
Add brandy and ignite.
Extinguish by covering pan after 30 seconds.
Add 1/4 cup parsley, remaining scallions and wine.
Boil 1 minute to reduce slightly.
Combine cornstarch and water; stir into sauce, simmering until thickened. Season with salt and pepper, if desired.
Serve sauce over patties.
Yields 7 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend together well.
Chill for at least 15 minutes.
Form balls the size of a walnut.
Mash with fork dipped in sugar, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen cookies.

title: aunt phyllis' carrot cake
directions: In large bowl, mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat after each.
Gradually add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Add carrots, coconut and nuts and mix.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: acini de pepe fruit salad
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients, cook and make custard. Cool.
Cook the acini de pepe in the water, oil and salt.
Drain and cool.
Mix with custard and refrigerate overnight.
Add the remaining ingredients to custard mixture.
Fruit is optional.
Can substitute other fruits. Freezes well.

title: dough for apple dumplings(makes about 8)
directions: Mix together.
Make 8 balls, roll and put 1/2 apple (any kind in each).
Sprinkle cinnamon on top, 1 teaspoon sugar and 1 dab butter in each.
Roll apple up and sprinkle more cinnamon and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli saladroswell, new mexico
directions: Chop and mix the broccoli and purple onion together.

title: coconut cornbread(1994 state fair of oklahoma)
directions: This cornbread is not recommended for beans, it's almost like eating white cake.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together well.
Heat shortening in skillet. Beat eggs and pour buttermilk into beaten eggs.
Pour this mixture into dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour shortening in this batter, mix it good.
Pour back into hot skillet.
Bake in a 400° oven until well browned.
Flip bread over in skillet to sweat it.
Turn oven off and put bread back into it for a few minutes.

title: lentil stew
directions: In a large 8-quart pot, cook lentils with 1 pint of water and salt.
Put all ingredients in pot.
Meanwhile, saute 2 large onions in 1 tablespoon olive oil and 3 tablespoons water.
Add to the pot when onions are soft.
Simmer for about 1 hour or until the vegetables are soft, not overcooked.
Stir occasionally.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese on Medium for 1 minute. Spread over the bottom of a 9 x 13 microwave-safe dish. Add chili and top with cheese. Microwave, covered, for 5 minutes. Dip into it with tortilla chips.

title: nevelle's peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour once before measuring, then sift again with soda and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and mix until smooth.
Add peanut butter, stir well, then add flour mixture.
Mix to a stiff dough and add vanilla.
Form into tiny balls and press onto greased cookie sheet.
