Press with back of fork for design.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen small cookies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo, add onions and broccoli.
Saute over medium heat. Stir.
Add soup, cheese and milk.
Remove from heat and add cooked rice and mix well.
Pour in buttered casserole dish and bake covered for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blonde's brownie pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar and flour.
Blend in eggs and melted butter.
Fold evenly the chocolate chips, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into an 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; serve warm or room temperature.
Enjoy.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together very well.

title: spud casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: garlic parmesan bread(total cooking time:  1 to 2 minutes)
directions: Mix butter and garlic.
Cut loaf into slices 1-inch thick without cutting all the way through the bottom crust.
Spread slices of bread with garlic butter, then sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Place loaf on microproof rack or on paper towels.
Cook on High (Maximum power) 1 to 2 minutes or until bread is heated through.
Makes 12 servings.

title: crazy quick cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Blend sifted dry ingredients with the oil, vanilla, vinegar and water.
Blend well and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: yeast buttermilk biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast.
Knead and store in refrigerator in an airtight container. Roll out desired amount and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Cook the sausage and beef until brown in skillet.
Add salt, pepper, bread crumbs and tomato sauce.
Cook until there is little grease on meat before adding this.
Put mixture on 1/2 of hamburger bun.
Use one slice Velveeta, cut in four equal squares. Put one piece on top of each bun.
Put in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: coffee bars
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spread on jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Frost while still warm.

title: sticky bunns
directions: Melt butter in a layer cake pan.
Add above ingredients to butter.
Sprinkle cinnamon.
Top with 10 refrigerator biscuits and bake as package directs or until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes. Turn onto plate.

title: baked cheese cake #1
directions: Mix together and pat in the bottom of a spring-form pan.

title: tipsy cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over medium heat. Stir in vegetables and cook until vegetables are tender crisp. Stir in flour, mustard and pepper; cook for 1 to 2 minutes.

Lower heat to medium-low. Gradually stir in half and half and broth. Cook, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes until soup is thickened. Add cheese and beer. Stir constantly until cheese is melted. Do not boil. Yields 7 cups.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix boiling water, 1/2 cup sugar and salt with butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and add 1 teaspoon sugar to yeast.
Stir yeast mixture into water and sugar and salt mixture.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour and beat thoroughly.
Brush top with some melted butter.
Cover tightly and store in refrigerator until next day.
Roll out and allow to raise until doubled.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields about 1 1/2 cups.

title: creamy tuna casserole
directions: Mix noodles, tuna, mushrooms, pimentos, sour cream, milk, salt and pepper in 2-quart container.
Cover loosely and microwave on Medium (50%) for 10 minutes; stir.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and margarine.
Sprinkle evenly over tuna mixture.
Microwave uncovered 4 to 7 minutes longer or until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: bean and beef dish
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Heat the baked beans while beef is browning.
After beef browns, drain the excess water then combine the beef and beans together in a casserole dish.
Bake for about 20 minutes.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Cream the sugar and butter; mix in flour and salt.
Press 3/4 of mixture into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Warm jam in microwave and spread over base.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked minestrone soup
directions: Combine beef, onion, garlic, salt, pepper and olive oil in large oven pan.
Toss to coat meat evenly and brown, uncovered, in hot oven (400°).
Add broth, water and Italian seasoning.
Cover; cook 1 hour until meat is almost tender.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, olives, carrots and macaroni.
Sprinkle zucchini on top.
Cover; return to oven for 40 to 45 minutes longer until macaroni is tender.
Makes about 3 1/2 quarts.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients.
Drop
on	ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for
10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbrown, or they will become tough.
If
desired,
split	biscuits open and use for shortcakes.

title: debbie krosofsky's banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Beat together eggs, sugar, oil, bananas, vanilla and syrup.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: homemade bread
directions: *Or use dry milk add add to the dry ingredients.
Add the 2 cups liquid to the water.

title: deviled crab casserole
directions: Combine crabmeat, 1 cup of bread crumbs, green pepper, parsley, chives and egg in a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish. Combine mayonnaise and next 6 ingredients; stir into crabmeat mixture.
Combine butter and remaining bread crumbs; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add milk, melted butter and vanilla.
Grease and flour Pyrex pie dish. Pour mixture in.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Allow ice cream to soften.
Mix ice cream, whipped cream and Slim Fast mix (for chocolate flavoring) until thoroughly mixed, and then spread mixture into pie crust.
Place in freezer at least 4 hours.

title: ham and sauerkraut casserole
directions: Mix ham, oats, onions, eggs and milk and shape in 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place sauerkraut, applesauce and caraway seed in bottom of casserole dish or 8-inch square pan.
Place ham rolls on top of kraut mixture. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: herb-roasted leg of lamb with red potatoes
directions: Mix wine, 1/2 cup lemon juice, 1 tablespoon olive oil, half of minced garlic, 1/2 tablespoon oregano and 1/2 tablespoon rosemary in small bowl.
Place lamb in large glass baking pan.
Pour wine mixture over.
Cover and refrigerate lamb overnight, turning occasionally.
Cook potatoes in large pot of boiling, salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Cut potatoes crosswise in half.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, peanut butter, eggs and water.
Add remainder of cake mix.
Mixture is really thick.
Take 2/3 of mixture and place in a spring-form cake pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Let it cool.
Cover with 2 quarts vanilla ice cream that has thawed. Layer top with your choice of toppings (cherries, hot fudge, nuts).
Place in freezer to set.

title: almost instant brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients, except English peas. Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Add peas and simmer another 5 minutes.

title: sauteed collard greens with garlic and scallions
directions: In a large nonstick skillet or a wok, heat oil over medium heat.
Add collards and garlic. Saute, stirring constantly until collards are just wilted, about 4 minutes.
Add scallions just before collards are finished cooking. Serve hot. Sprinkle with Feta cheese. Serves 4.

title: lemon custard pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, flour, milk and lemon. Fold in egg whites (beaten).
Put in well-greased and floured custard cups.
Bake in 1/2 inch water for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruits thoroughly.
Add marshmallows.
Mix with sour cream and refrigerate overnight.

title: coffee cake
directions: Beat ingredients 4 minutes at medium speed.
Put half of dough in greased angel food cake pan.
Mix 5 tablespoons sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle half on dough and swirl.
Put on rest of dough; sprinkle other half of sugar and cinnamon mixture and swirl.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 1 hour before cutting.

title: cracklin' cornbread
directions: Mix meal, baking powder, salt and soda with the cracklins'. Add eggs and clabber; stir until mixed.
Pour in a greased pan and bake in a hot oven until done.

title: cinderella crisps
directions: Using 2 forks, roll bread strips in milk, coating all sides. Roll in coconut.
Place on well-greased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove at once from baking sheet. Serves 24.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Crumble sausage and mix all ingredients; form into small balls.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer and cook immediately for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's noodles
directions: Use any multiples of this combination for the amount you need. Mix.
Roll thin onto floured surface.
Partially dry; cut into strips.
Turn cut noodles over and finish drying.
Do not use salt in dough for light, tender noodles.

title: summer squash in sour cream
directions: Cut squash into 1/4 inch crosswise slices.
Cook in boiling water for 3 minutes and drain (dry).
Heat butter and cook onion until soft.
Add the dill seed, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute. Add squash and cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Mix soup and water and pour over chicken.
Mix together flour, buttermilk and melted margarine.
Pour this batter over chicken mixture.
Add chicken broth over batter.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour (crust rises to top and is golden brown).

title: brie wafers
directions: Mix Brie, butter, flour, cayenne pepper and seasoning salt well.
Separate into long rolls wrapped in wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm; cut in 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick slices.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake on sheets at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes; cool and store in airtight containers.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw and spread out hash browns into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, sprayed with cooking spray.
Mix remaining ingredients, except for corn flakes or crackers.
Pour mixture over hash browns; top with crumbled corn flakes or crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rye party squares
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on rye squares.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Broil ever so slightly, just enough to melt.
Serve hot.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased dish and cover with cheese.
Mix can of soup with milk; pour over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle dry dressing mix over all.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian zucchini pie
directions: Combine zucchini, onions and butter; simmer for 10 minutes. Add spices to zucchini.
Combine eggs and cheese; add to zucchini. Press rolls into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with mustard.
Pour zucchini mixture over rolls.
Bake at 370° for 18 to 20 minutes. Cover with foil the last 10 minutes.

title: slomp
directions: In a deep porcelain or glass baking dish, put the cup of sugar over unsweetened rhubarb or berries and stir to cover all.
Mix remaining ingredients and just pour over mixture in baking dish and spread on top of fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot topped with cream.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Grease cookie sheet. Pat crescent rolls out and bake at 350° until brown.
Let cool completely.

title: corn bread
directions: Put meal, sugar, salt, water and margarine in large saucepan. Boil until thickened.
Add eggs and milk.
Take off burner and add baking powder.
Stir well.
Pour in greased pan and bake at 350 degrees for approximately 40 minutes.

title: heath brunch coffee cake
directions: Blend flour, margarine and sugar.
Take out 1/2 cup of mixture.
To the rest, add buttermilk, soda, egg and vanilla. Blend well.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Sprinkle topping over the batter and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: honey nut bread
directions: Mix together.
Put into greased floured pan.
Let stand about 1 hour.
Bake in a slow oven about 40 minutes to an hour.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients, except cake mix, butter and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into pan.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix; drizzle with melted butter.
Cover with chopped nuts.
Bake 1 hour.

title: creamy ham and broccoli(4 to 6 servings)
directions: If desired, coat inside of a slow cooker with nonstick spray. In slow cooker, place ham, broccoli, soup, cheese spread, water chestnuts, rice, milk, celery, onion and pepper.
Stir until blended.
Smooth top, pushing rice into mixture.
Cover and cook on high for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or on low for 4 to 5 hours or until rice and onion are tender, stirring occasionally if possible.
If desired, sprinkle with paprika before serving.
Serve with sliced beets or tomatoes and a relish plate.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Place all in crock-pot and cook 3 hours or longer.
Serve over rice or rolls.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into pie pan.
Cook for 45 minutes at 300°.
Top with whipped cream (if desired).

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Pour in pie crust and chill.

title: cranberry and jello salad
directions: Mix jello and 2 cups hot water until jello is dissolved.
Put in refrigerator until it starts to set up.
Add mayonnaise and cranberry sauce; beat well with electric mixer.
Keep refrigerated.
Very good.

title: clam-avocado bisque
directions: Blend all ingredients in order and chill.
Serve in chilled soup dishes.
Size of avocado controls consistency.
Add more stock if needed for desired consistency.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: french green lentil salad
directions: Cook lentils and add all but last 4 ingredients in 4 cups of water for 30 minutes.
Drain lentils well.
Remove bay leaf, garlic and thyme.
Keep lentils warm and whisk together last 4 ingredients.
Add lentils to dressing and serve warm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix the flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in the cream cheese and butter until it has a corn meal consistency. Stir in the sour cream until pastry holds together.
Form into a ball.
Wrap and refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Roll out on floured surface and cut into 3-inch rounds.
Place preserves on bottom half.
Moisten edges and fold over.
Press edges with a fork to seal.
Prick the top with fork and bake at 325°.

title: canned east texas salsa
directions: Wash and remove stem ends and cut tomatoes into quarters.
Mix all but vinegar, sugar and salt into an 8 to 10-quart pot.
Bring to boil and cook 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Put tomato mixture through food mill or coarse sieve.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt and return to boil.
Simmer 30 minutes or until mixture is desired consistency.
Pour hot tomato sauce into hot canning jars (1-pint size), leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Put on lids.
Process for 10 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: chicken vegetable stir-fry
directions: In small bowl, stir together cornstarch, broth, soy sauce and ginger until smooth; set aside.
In 10-inch skillet or wok over medium-high heat in 1 tablespoon hot oil, stir-fry half of the chicken until browned.
Remove and set aside.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
Reduce heat to medium.
In same skillet in remaining 1 tablespoon hot oil, stir-fry vegetables and garlic until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add reserved cornstarch mixture.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Return chicken to skillet.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased), "dump" pie filling mixed with spices and pecans.
Top with dry cake mix.
Add crushed pineapple and top with remaining nuts.
Add more cinnamon and brown sugar. Cut in butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan and lightly flour bottom of pan.

title: granola
directions: Heat oil, honey and vanilla in saucepan until warm.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour
honey mixture over dry ingredients until all is coated (okay to use hands to mix). Spread granola on shallow greased pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour or at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Store in airtight containers or Baggies.

title: baked squash with cheese
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain. Fill casserole with layers of squash, onions and cheese. Sprinkle with salt and pepper on each layer. Dot with butter and cover. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jalapeno pepper potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil until just done and drain.
In large mixing bowl, mix potatoes, shredded cheese, mayonnaise and peppers.
Use just enough mayonnaise to make mixture thick (not creamy).
Spoon into oblong baking dish (spray with Pam).
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes until golden brown on top.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In a large skillet, saute sliced onion and bacon to golden brown.
Mix the tomato paste and saute for 5 more minutes.
Add stew meat and sweet Hungarian paprika.
Cook slowly in meat juices for 15 minutes. Add caraway seed and lemon zest.
Cover skillet and cook until meat is tender.
Before serving, mix in sour cream. Serve over egg noodles.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple, reserving liquid; halve slices.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and brown sugar slowly in skillet.
Beat eggs, add sugar and butter.
Blend alternately, the juice and flour with the beaten eggs and sugar.
Place pineapple in melted sugar and butter.
Maraschino cherries (halved) may be place in hole of pineapple rings.
Chopped nuts can be used also. Pour batter over the mixture and bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Servings: 8.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients except tea bags in large pot.
Bring mixture to boil; boil 4 to 5 minutes.
Add tea bags and let sit 10 minutes.
Remove tea bags, cloves and cinnamon.
Serve hot.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Use dough hooks for this recipe.
Put yeast in lukewarm water with 2 teaspoons sugar in a lukewarm bowl.
Leave set 15 to 20 minutes.
Scald milk.
Beat eggs well, then add eggs to cooled milk mixture.
In mixing bowl, put sugar, oleo, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and vanilla.
Cream mixture well.
Add warm milk mixture.
Beat well.
Add yeast.
Beat well.
Add sifted flour, 1 cup at a time. Put in well-greased large bowl.
Let rise overnight in refrigerator.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix together and pack into greased ring mold.
Chill; unmold and serve with crackers.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Then set aside to cool.
Beat and mix eggs, sour cream, salt and cheese.
Pour all these ingredients in pie shell.
Crumble crisp bacon on top.

title: cheddar bread bake
directions: Combine Bisquick and cheese.
Add milk and eggs (just enough to moisten).
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Best served warm.

title: slush
directions: Boil water and sugar for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients to sugar-water and mix well.
Put in freezer.
Stir every 8 hours.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix well by hand.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Let stand for 2 hours.

title: pepper steak
directions: Marinate beef in mixture of oil, cornstarch, soy sauce, salt and pepper for about an hour.
Brown beef in wok or frypan.
When browned, push beef to wok ledge.
Wok onions and peppers in a small amount of oil until onions are browned.
Mix cornstarch and water and add to vegetables.
Return beef to wok.
Cover and cook until desired tenderness.
Serve over rice.

title: hamburgers
directions: Mix well and pat into patties.

title: tuna puff
directions: Beat egg yolks and combine with tuna fish. Stir in onion flakes, mustard and pepper. Mix well. Beat egg whites with salt until stiff; fold into tuna mixture. Bake in preheated 450° oven 20 minutes.

title: veal saltimbocca
directions: Cut veal
cutlets
into
5-inch
pieces.
Sprinkle each piece of veal with a little sage.
Place a piece of Prosciutto on each piece of
veal
and secure with a toothpick.
Heat oil and 1 tablespoon butter
in
skillet
on high heat.
When hot, cook veal for a few
minutes
on
each
side until the veal is well browned. Add water
to
pan
and scrape bottom, making a gravy.
Add the rest
of the butter and parsley; mix well over low heat.
Pour gravy over veal and serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: reba's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, syrup and vanilla. Add the pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Dot with butter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375° or until almost set.

title: baked chicken poupon
directions: Mix mustard, oil, garlic powder and Italian seasoning in a large plastic bag. Add chicken and shake to coat. Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 25 minutes or until done. Makes 4 servings.

title: fried cawsway(burmese spaghetti)
directions: Brown the onion; add meat and spices.
When fully cooked, cut tomatoes in small pieces and add.
Cover with water and simmer until it's well cooked.
Add to spaghetti and stir.
Garnish with cabbage and green onions.

title: rolls
directions: Add the sugar and salt to milk and shortening, cool to lukewarm.
Add softened yeast and eggs to the milk.
Add enough flour to make a soft batter and then add enough to make a soft dough.
Turn on a lightly floured board and knead until right consistency.
Place in a greased pan and turn over.
Let rise until doubled, punch down and let rise again.
Make dough into rolls.

title: roast pork marinade
directions: Sprinkle salt and meat tenderizer.
Rub all over the roast. Mix sugar, salt, garlic pepper, cooking wine, catsup, food coloring and Accent all together in a bowl large enough to hold roast, covered.
Put roast to marinate and refrigerate 24 hours, turning occasionally.
Cook on a broiler pan on a rack, uncovered.
Bake in 350° oven.
Use meat thermometer when beginning cooking to ensure doneness.

title: angie's spaghetti dinner
directions: Peel
eggplant,
shred	and
place in 8-quart saucepan. Add tomatoes,
sauce and paste;
simmer about 30 minutes.
Add prepared
sauce,
sugar, Italian seasoning and parsley flakes. Cover and
simmer
hour.
In a heavy skillet, saute chopped onion in
olive
oil.
Add ground beef and garlic salt; brown. Add to	sauce;	cover
and
simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add mushrooms and wine,
if
desired,
the
last 30 minutes of cooking time. Serve over vermicelli, thin spaghetti or pasta of your choice, cooked by package
directions.
Serves 8 to 12.
Unused sauce and cooked pasta may be frozen separately for later use.

title: golden puffs(similar to donut holes)
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and nutmeg. Beat together slightly cooking oil, milk and egg.
Stir all together with a fork until thoroughly mixed. Drop by teaspoon into hot fat. Drain and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: biscuits
directions: Set oven at 425°.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in butter with a potato masher (works best) or fork, leaving little cubes in the flour mixture.
Break egg into 1 cup measure, fill cup with milk and beat together.
Pat out on floured board, cut in size desired (a regular drinking glass works well).
Place biscuits on ungreased cookie sheet, touching each other.
Bake until golden (15 minutes or so, I think.)

title: three bean chili
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomatoes and tomato sauce, in a 3 to 4-quart slow cooker. Cover and cook on low heat setting for 8 to 10 hours. Stir in tomatoes and tomato sauce. Increase heat setting to high. Cover and cook 5 minutes or until heated through. Makes 8 (1-cup) servings.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs, vanilla and confectioners sugar.
Pour over base.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: hamburger and cabbage casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions, then place 3 cups cabbage in well-buttered casserole dish.
Add hamburger and onions.
Place remaining cabbage on top.
Pour tomato soup over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours in covered casserole dish.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a greased casserole dish (9x13) cube bread pieces.
Spread crumbled sausage and cheese over the bread pieces.
In a separate bowl combine the eggs, cream, mustard and salt and pepper together. Mix well.
Pour egg mixture over the bread, sausage and cheese in the casserole dish.
Let this sit overnight in the refrigerator. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 - 1 1/2 hours.
Enjoy with fresh fruit.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and butter and pour in greased and floured cake pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs, powdered sugar and pecans. Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 325° until done, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tomato juice salad
directions: Boil 1 cup water and dissolve Jell-O in it. Add tomato juice and cool until it begins to thicken. Add remaining ingredients and pour into molds. Serve on lettuce leaves with Ranch dressing. Double for larger recipe.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Place sauce, vegetables, peas and water in large skillet. Cover and simmer 10 minutes until tender.
Stir in cheese.
Spoon over pasta.

title: mocha frosting
directions: Blend with an electric mixer.

title: mulled grape juice
directions: Mix juice, water and sugar in saucepan.
Tie spices in small cheesecloth bag and to liquid, add, boil and stir and allow to stand over very low heat for 10 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Bring again to boil.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt, soda and cinnamon; add to creamed mixture. Then add apples and nuts; mix well.
Pour into loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 325°. Makes 2 loaves.

title: fried okra(afro-american favorite)
directions: Cut off the top stems; hand wash the okra, discarding any that are dry and woody.
If the okras are large, cut on a diagonal into 1-inch lengths.
If they are small, leave them whole.
Dip in the beaten egg and roll or shake in cornmeal seasoned with salt and pepper.
Fry in hot oil or bacon fat until golden brown. Makes 6 servings.

title: tomato juice(very similar to v-8)
directions: Slice all vegetables and boil until you can run them through a sieve.
Add honey and salt.
Mix well and pour into canning jars. Process for 20 minutes in a boiling water bath.

title: good cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.

title: veal or chicken parmesan
directions: In shallow bowl, combine bread crumbs, cheese, oregano, salt and pepper.
Pound cutlets very thin.
Dip cutlets in egg and coat with bread crumbs.
Fry in 1/3 cup oil, adding oil as necessary. Keep warm in 150° oven.

title: let's have a party ham roll-ups
directions: In small bowl, mix cream cheese, milk, parsley, onions and nuts.
Spread thin layer on boiled ham slices.
With cheese side up and beginning at short side, roll up each slice.
Chill several hours until firm.
Cut rolls with a sharp knife into 1/2-inch slices.
To hold and make easier to eat, put a toothpick through each one.
Arrange on party tray.
Garnish with white grapes or bowl of olives.
This makes 80 small slices.

title: diet vegetable soup
directions: Mix together in a large saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until cabbage is tender.
Very low in calories.
Eat as much as you like.

title: pear preserves
directions: Pour
sugar
over
pears and let set few hours or overnight. Cook
slowly until syrup is thickened.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: cinnamon swirl salad
directions: Dissolve jello and candies in boiling water.
Stir in applesauce, lemon juice and salt.
Chill until set.
Fold in pecans and pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Mix and cook all of these ingredients together over hot water. Work them into a smooth paste and whip them until fluffy.
Serve the fondue at once.
Goes great with melba toast.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: creole champagne punch
directions: Peel and quarter the pineapple.
Grate two quarters of pineapple on a large grater with tear drop shaped holes.
Set aside.
Cut remaining 2 quarters into large chunks (1/2 inch by 1 1/2 inch wedges).
Set aside.
Prepare strawberries.
If frozen, thaw and drain berries and save juice.
If fresh, rinse and pat dry.
Shortly before serving, combine sugar, lemon juice and orange juice (strawberry juice if frozen berries used) in punch bowl.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Add champagne and soda.
Carefully place ice in punch bowl, then stir in grated pineapple wedges and strawberries.

title: taco pasta casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, brown ground beef and drain excess liquid. Add taco seasoning spices as directed on the package and stir to blend; reserve.

title: pork chops stacks
directions: Arrange chops in single layer in a shallow baking dish; sprinkle with salt.
Place an onion slice, then a lemon slice on top of each.
Stir brown sugar into chili sauce in a small bowl; spoon over chops.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake an additional 15 minutes, or until chops are tender.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread pecans on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam. Layer coconut on top of nuts.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions and pour over coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese together over low heat.
Pour in confectioners sugar and stir until smooth.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken or turkey pot pie
directions: Boil meat and vegetables just until done; drain.
Combine soup, milk and seasonings.
Pour over meat mixture and mix.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover with second pie crust and pinch edges. Bake at 450° for about 15 to 20 minutes, until crust is golden brown.
Let set for 20 minutes before slicing.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Using electric mixer on low, mix 1 quart milk, eggs and sugar, adding other ingredients and pour in a 1 1/2-gallon electric ice cream freezer. Fruit of your choice may be added before freezing. Peach is our favorite.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: fresh tomato cake
directions: Cream together the brown sugar and shortening.
Add the eggs and next 5 ingredients.
Stir in and mix well the tomatoes, nuts, dates and raisins.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until done.
Use cream cheese icing.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Cook cake according to package directions.
Cook milk and sugar until sugar is dissolved, then pour over cake.
Spread cool whip on cake when it is cooled.
Add coconut on top.
Refrigerate.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello per instructions on box; let cool.
Just before jello begins to
set, stir in cranberry sauce, nuts and mandarin oranges.
Stir jello several times to keep fruit from coming to the top.

title: dump cake
directions: In 13 x 9-inch ungreased cake pan, put pie filling.
Add pineapple.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix on top.
Cut butter into slices and place on top of cake mix.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with hands and form a ball. Roll in chopped pecans and chill in refrigerator for at least 1 hour. Serve with Wheat Thin crackers.

title: microwave recipe for all other duncan hines cakes(except butter recipe and angel food)
directions: Empty cake mix into a large bowl.
Add eggs, hot water, Crisco oil and vanilla.
Beat with fork until smooth and thick about 200 strokes.
Pour half of batter into microwave safe cake pan.
If small pan is used, do not pour more than half full.
Microwave 6 to 7 minutes on High.
Longer for low wattage ovens.
Cake is done when it pulls away from sides of dish and top is dry.
If not done, continue baking at 30 second intervals until done.
Repeat with second layer.
Bake 1 layer at a time.
De-pan immediately onto serving plate.
Let cool 5 to 15 minutes.
Frost and cover tightly.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars, shortening and eggs.
Add the flour, salt and soda.
Mix together.
Add vanilla and chips.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix molasses and milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add eggs and stir in shortening.
Beat until the mixture is smooth and creamy.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: fruit dip refresher
directions: Combine all ingredients, except fruit dippers. Mix well; chill. Serve with fruit dippers.

title: orange whip
directions: Cook ginger ale to boil, then add jello and add all ingredients.
Chill!

title: grilled chicken salad
directions: For vinaigrette, in a screw-top jar, combine oil, vinegar, dill weed, garlic, pepper and oregano. Cover and shake well. Let stand 1 hour.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix and chill several hours.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix all together.
Slice a loaf of French bread.
Spread mixture on one side of all pieces.
Toast at 425° for 10 minutes or until golden brown and cheese is melted.

title: baked zucchini halves
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash zucchini; cut in half lengthwise. Sprinkle cut side of zucchini with Vege-Sal or other seasoned salt.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Brush a small amount of olive oil on each.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: christmas pecan cake
directions: Combine pecans, pineapple and cherries in a large bowl.
Sift the flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add to fruit and nuts.
Toss mixture with hands so that fruit is evenly coated. Mix eggs with vanilla; pour over fruit.
Mix thoroughly as the mixture is quite stiff.
Press into a well-greased 9 x 3-inch loaf pan lined with waxed paper and greased.
Bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan on a rack.
Remove and wrap in plastic wrap and foil.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps for a year.
Slice thin to serve.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Prepare
pie
shell
and
refrigerate.
Preheat oven to 350°. In
medium bowl with mixer, beat eggs well.
Add sugar, corn syrup, flour, salt and vanilla; beat until well combined. Stir in butter and
pecans;
mix
well.
Turn
into pie shell. Bake 60 minutes or until filling is set in center when shaken.

title: harvard beets
directions: Melt margarine, add cornstarch, sugar and salt; then add vinegar and beets and heat until thickened.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Melt butter, add garlic.
Mix bread crumbs, parmesan cheese, pepper, and cheddar cheese in a bowl.
Dip chicken in garlic butter, then dip in bread crumb mixture, coating well.
Tuck ends under and put into baking dish (best when dish is crowded so chicken doesn't dry out).
Pour any extra butter and coating mixture over chicken.
Bake uncovered in a 9 x 13 baking dish at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle diced apples with lemon juice.
Combine with celery and mayonnaise to moisten.
Add raisins and Cool Whip.
Stir in walnuts just before serving.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: layered cabbage lasagna
directions: Cut up cabbage and put in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan; set aside. Brown ground chuck, onion, garlic, salt and pepper to taste; then pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle rice over meat mixture.
Combine in pan and bring to boil tomato sauce, soup and water; then pour over rice.
Cover with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover with tinfoil if cheese gets too brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in water until tender or about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Add 1/2 of dressing mix and salt.
Put in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with remaining dressing mix.
Melt margarine and drizzle on top. Bake about 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: green bean salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together corn oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Add beans, celery, onion, parsley, pimento and pickle relish.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Wash vegetables and cut up in chunks.
Mix in herbs.
Pour oil over mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° in the oven for approximately 45 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: darrel's manhandler casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Add cooked and drained noodles.
Mix well.
Put in large casserole dish; cook 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Serves a crowd.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour, milk and beaten egg yolks in sauce pan. Cook until thick, stirring often. Add vanilla. Layer graham crackers bananas and mixture in dish. Let cool and serve.

title: baked fish
directions: Slice fish into 1-inch slices.
Put into baking dish.
Add enough milk to just top fish.
Cover with 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup Italian bread crumbs.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until crusty brown at 350°.

title: special potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake covered at 375° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes more.

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream shortening, sugar, water and vanilla.
Beat in the eggs.
Combine flour, cocoa, salt and baking soda.
Gradually add to creamed mixture and beat just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts, if desired.

title: sausage vegetable casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with nonstick spray.
Press potatoes in bottom of dish, put vegetables on top and then cut up sausage pieces.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over mixture.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 1 hour.
Serve with biscuits.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar
and milk for 3 minutes.
Cool pan to touch. (20 minutes).
Beat
in
peanut butter and marshmallow cream. Pour into pan and cool.
Makes 2 pounds of fabulous candy.

title: church chicken and rice
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle rice over bottom.
Mix milk and soup.
Pour over rice.
Stir with fork; lay chicken on top. Sprinkle with onion soup; mix.
Seal with foil, tight.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat. Add next 6 ingredients to meat. Simmer, uncovered, until thick, 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in the milk, melted butter and vanilla; mix well.
In a small bowl, mix the sugar, brown sugar and cocoa.
Sprinkle the dry mixture over the batter in pan.
Pour water over all; do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pool room slaw
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, vinegar and black pepper.
Add mustard and vegetables.
Simmer, stirring constantly about 15 minutes. Cool.
Keeps in refrigerator several months.

title: danny's camp stew
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put all ingredients in a large crock pot and let cook all day on low heat.
(Use the whole bottle of hot ketchup if you want it real hot.)

title: baked beans hot dish
directions: Saute bacon and onion together.
Brown ground beef in same pan.
Combine beans with rest of the ingredients in casserole dish.
Pour bacon, onion and hamburger over beans and mix together.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in loaf pan (7 x 11-inch).
Mix rest of ingredients to make batter.
Pour over melted butter.
Add 1 large can pie filling fruit over top of batter.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: old testament cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add honey and beaten egg yolks.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Mix alternately with milk.
Stir in fruits and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites last.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: granny's graham cracker bars
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, milk and egg. Bring to boil, then cool. Add crushed graham crackers, coconut and nuts.
Put layer of whole crackers on cookie sheet.
Spread filling over crackers, then another layer of whole crackers.
Spread top with thin powdered sugar frosting.
Use cookie sheet, approximately 10 x 14-inch.

title: german potato salad(hot)
directions: Boil potatoes until tender. Peel and dice. Mix potatoes with other ingredients. Put in a casserole dish. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Cook in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients until moist and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven until almost brown.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together; set aside.
Blend together margarine, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add eggs, sour cream, milk, vanilla and bananas.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Divide fish into four servings.
Place fish in single layer in sprayed baking dish with thin ends turned under.
Brush fish with soy sauce.
In small bowl, combine bread crumbs, oleo and orange peel; sprinkle over fish.
Bake at 450° for 4 to 6 minutes per 1/2-inch thickness.

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Spoon whipped topping evenly into 6 dessert dishes.
Using a spoon, spread whipped topping into the bottom and up sides of each dish.
Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened.
Spoon pudding into center of "cloud."
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Best if made and eaten the same day.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread extra Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with any extra nuts.
May garnish with maraschino cherries. Refrigerate.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix squash, egg, onion, milk, flour, salt, pepper and baking powder into batter.
Drop batter by the spoonful into hot oil and fry 3 to 5 minutes until golden brown.
Turn each fritter once. Remove to paper towel.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: green pepper soup
directions: Simmer until vegetables are cooked, then add the rice. Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.

title: quick microwave fudge
directions: Mix confectioners sugar and cocoa.
Pour in a bowl.
Slice butter into 5 or 6 chunks.
Place butter in bowl.
Add other ingredients and cook in microwave for 3 minutes.
Stir well and pour in dish to cool.

title: quick brownies
directions: Sift all ingredients together.
Use self-rising flour.
Pour in pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: pie crust for fruit pies
directions: Cut Crisco into flour and divide into 10 balls.
Makes 10 fried pies.
Knott's Berry peach preserves is a good filling and can be bought at Sam's.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into pieces (can use cocktail sausages).
Mix all ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve immediately.

title: california crunch
directions: Mix together cabbage and green onions. Brown in oil, using as much as you like, the slivered almonds and sesame seed.
When cool, toss with cabbage.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix together and put in loaf pan (greased).
Bake about 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: easy rocky road
directions: Microwave chips and peanut butter for 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over marshmallows and chopped peanuts.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: quick eggnog
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well 5 minutes in electric mixer.
Refrigerate 8 to 10 hours before serving.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix eggs with mixer.
Add sugar slowly, until stiff.
Fold in crackers, pecans, baking powder and vanilla. Put in a buttered pie pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
When cool, cover with Cool Whip.

title: celery soup
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add onions and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add flour and stir.
Add broth and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and add cream, Tabasco and pepper.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Scramble sausage in heavy skillet just until lightly brown. Drain on paper towel.
Pour off part of the grease and saute onions, celery and pepper until clear.
Boil rice with water and soup mix for 7 minutes.
Combine with sausage and vegetables.
Put in casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Slivered almonds may be sprinkled on top.
This is a delicious supper dish with green salad and French bread.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, lemon juice and milk together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and fold into cool graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve cold.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and onion together.
Drain well. Mix in both cans of soup.
Spray Pam on a 9 x 13 pan and arrange Tater Tots in single layer.
Top with beef and soup mixture.

title: mom's rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix oleo, sugar, eggs, buttermilk, soda, vanilla and salt.
Add flour and rhubarb mix.
Pour into greased pan.
Mix brown sugar and nuts; sprinkle over top.
Bake 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: doughnut puffs
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add to mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.

title: french apple squares
directions: Mix flour, shortening, sugar and salt.
Blend in egg yolk and milk.
Roll out half of dough to fit medium size (low cut) pan. Spread with Wilderness fruit filling and dot with butter.
Cover with top crust and brush with egg white.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Glaze with powdered sugar icing.

title: orange blossom punch
directions: Place orange juice and sherbet in a punch bowl.
Slowly add ginger ale.
Float slices of orange with a maraschino cherry in center in the punch bowl.
Add ice cubes.
Yields 15 to 20 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: chinese marinade
directions: Pierce 2 to 3 pounds of meat.
Pour on marinade.
Marinate at room temperature for 24 to 48 hours.
Cook as desired.
Especially good on the grill.

title: creamy turkey-vegetable casserole
directions: In a small skillet, saute onion, green or red pepper and mushrooms in butter until onion is tender.
In a large bowl, mix soups, milk, sherry and pepper.
Stir in sauteed mixture, vegetables and turkey.
Turn into greased shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish; sprinkle with noodles.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: In large pot, combine orange juice, cinnamon sticks and water; start to simmer.
When tea is brewed, add to orange juice.
Then add the rest of the ingredients and simmer over very low fire. Serve piping hot.

title: oven-roasted veggies
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In plastic bag, toss all ingredients until coated well.
Empty into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake, stirring once, 20 minutes or until veggies are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour half of mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan (use cookie sheet).
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: grilled eggplant
directions: Combine all the ingredients for the marinade.
Place in a flat-bottomed pan, such as a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Place the eggplant slices in the pan.
Allow the slices to soak on each side for at least 10 minutes per side.
Grill over hot coals until soft. Occasionally drizzle with the marinade.
When eggplant is very tender, serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Put spinach in a 9 x 13 dish.
Cover with onions and mushrooms. Top with sliced tomato.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and cooked crumbled bacon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Could be used for a brunch or a vegetable dish.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon (not crisp) and place in casserole.
Saute cut-up green pepper and cut-up onion and place in casserole.
Drain pinto beans, kidney beans and green beans.
Do not drain pork and beans. Add beans to casserole along with sugar and catsup.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: taco salad
directions: First Layer:
One medium sour cream and 1 package taco seasoning.

title: one hundred year old raisin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Set aside.

title: sweet hot mustard
directions: Combine mustard, black pepper, white pepper and water.
Beat until smooth, then add the sugar, vinegar and salt.
Beat the eggs until fluffy and add to the mixture with the butter.
Boil 5 minutes until thick in heavy pot, stirring constantly (burns easily).
Cool and bottle.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes one (1) quart.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix broccoli, cauliflower and onion.
Make a dressing of remaining ingredients.
Pour dressing over vegetables.
Toss well and chill several hours or overnight.
Toss again before serving. Serves 8.

title: chicken bake
directions: Combine soups, rice and milk in large flat baking dish. Arrange chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over top and cover.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: cookies and cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round cake pans.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except cookies.
Mix until blended.
Stir in crushed cookies.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until tests done.
Cool.

title: linguine with fresh asparagus
directions: Cook asparagus in a small amount of water in saucepan for 3 minutes.
Drain; rinse under cold water.
Combine mustard, olive oil, onion, garlic, thyme, anchovy paste and parsley in a bowl; mix well.
Cook linguine according to package directions.
Drain. Combine linguine with dressing and asparagus in a serving bowl. Season with salt and pepper.
Serve warm or at room temperature. Serves 4.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix yeast in 1/3 cup warm water.
Cut shortening into flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Mix them, then knead, roll and cut like any other biscuits.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for several days.
Bake at 400° until brown, about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple brunch cakes(taste like sweet rolls from the bakery)
directions: In a small mixer bowl, combine cream cheese and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla; stir in crushed pineapple.
Split and toast English muffins; place on baking sheet.
Spoon pineapple mixture atop, using about 1 1/2 tablespoons mixture for each.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake in a 375° oven for 6 to 8 minutes. Serve warm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream butter, sugars and peanut butter together. Add egg and vanilla, mix well. Combine flour, oats, baking soda and salt. Stir into creamed mixture. Spread into Greased 9 X 13 pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool 10 minutes. Drizzle icing over bars.

title: potatoes romanoffwestboro, missouri
directions: Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Uncover and bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Freezes well.
Extend baking time when frozen.

title: salsa
directions: Wash vegetables and cut into very small pieces (except tomatoes).
Wash tomatoes and dip in hot water to remove skin. Put everything in big pot to cook at slow temperature until it starts to boil.
Wash jars and lids and sterilize.
Fill jars with mix.
Cook for about 45 minutes in canning pots.

title: mandarin orange pie
directions: Mix milk and sour cream.
Add Cool Whip, oranges and Tang. Pour in 2 large graham cracker crusts.
Let chill 3 hours.

title: cheesy garlic bread
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese, onions and garlic.
Spread on bread halves.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Wrap each half in foil and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours or can freeze.
Unwrap and place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes, 20 if frozen.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Soak chicken in salt water for a while.
Remove from water and dry with paper towels.
Place breasts on waxed paper.
Salt and pepper on each side.
Dip in melted butter and then roll in potato chips.
Place in foil lined baking pan.
Cover with foil and seal.
Bake in 350 degree oven for one hour or more depending on thickness of breasts.

title: ham and corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; add onion and celery; saute until golden.
Sprinkle with flour.
Stir in broth and potatoes.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add corn, milk and ham.
Simmer until it just starts to bubble; do not boil.
Season with salt and pepper.
(Even better the second day!)

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all but the ginger ale.
Put in freezer and let partially freeze.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine salt, mustard, chili sauce, onion, parsley and salad dressing.
Marinate cooked macaroni in mixture 15 minutes.
Add shrimp, eggs and cucumber.
Toss together lightly.
Chill well. Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Make a thick batter from pancake mix and evaporated milk. Soak onion slices in ice water until crisp.
Dip in batter and fry in oil until golden brown.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream shortening, vanilla and sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with cracker crumbs and milk.
Fold in egg whites and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.	Check for doneness with toothpick.

title: apple dabble cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet mandarin butter
directions: Drain peel and chop.
Mix peel, juice, sugar and butter. Cover and refrigerate.

title: baked apricot casserole
directions: Grease baking dish with butter.
Place a layer of apricots in dish.
Sprinkle with half of the brown sugar and half of the crackers.
Dot with half of butter.
Place another layer of apricots and rest of crackers, then brown sugar.
Top with remaining butter.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until bubbly hot. Serves 10 to 12.

title: quick and easy stromboli
directions: Remove bread from freezer; let thaw.
Let bread rise; punch it down and roll into rectangle, approximately 11 x 7-inches.
Layer salami, pepperoni, ham and cheese over the dough.
Sprinkle with garlic, oregano and Parmesan.
Roll up dough jelly roll fashion. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and slice about 1 inch thick.
Serves 8 or slice thin for appetizer.

title: hen on the nest
directions: Cook, skin and cut up chicken.
Mix together undiluted cream of chicken soup with yogurt and lemon juice.
Saute mushrooms and celery until tender.
Add mushrooms, celery and cooked chicken to chicken soup mixture.
Layer in baking dish.
Heat at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with cooked peas.
Serve.
Serves 6.

title: mary's coconut pecan squares
directions: Bake in sheet pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: magic mayo-dressing
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Place ingredients in a bowl. Beat with hand mixer or electric mixer.
Pour into pint jar and place in refrigerator until ready to use.
Number of people to serve is 2.
One teaspoon of ingredient, add milk to thin.
More if needed.

title: baked bean wieners
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato chowder
directions: Saute bacon and onion in large kettle.
Add potatoes, celery, carrots, water, bouillon cube and seasonings.
Cover and cook until vegies are tender.
Add milk and heat through.
Mix flour and butter.
Add to chowder.
Cook, stirring occasionally until slightly thick.

title: barley v-8 soup
directions: Slowly boil all ingredients, except barley, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Then simmer for 1/2 hour or more.
During last 20 minutes of simmering, add barley.

title: aunt vera's lemon chess pie
directions: Blend and pour in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn oven temperature down to 350° and bake another 10 minutes.
Do not overbake (the 2 oven settings will prevent the crust from becoming soggy).

title: salmon patties erma
directions: In a bowl, clean salmon; mash with fork and grate in an onion with its juice, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, parsley, garlic powder, seasoned salt and egg.
Add enough dry bread crumbs until you can shape patties.
Fry in stickproof pan on medium heat until brown on both sides, about 15 minutes.

title: squash pickle
directions: Combine squash and onions; sprinkle with salt.
Let stand one hour.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pack squash and onions into hot jars leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Cover at once with lids and screw tight.
Process in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 pints.

title: special lamb shanks
directions: Brown lamb shanks in oil in heavy skillet.
While shanks are browning, lightly oil large casserole.
Place garlic, onions and carrots in bottom of casserole.
Transfer browned shanks to casserole in single layer.
Add bay leaves, oregano and thyme. Pour stewed tomatoes over shanks.
Cover.
Place in 350° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add water if necessary during cooking.
Serves 3 to 6.

title: swedish coffee bread
directions: Add butter, sugar and salt to scalded milk.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large mixer bowl.
Sprinkle in dry yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Stir until dissolved, add cardamon, lukewarm milk mixture, eggs and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in additional flour to make a smooth dough. Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise for 2 hours.
Turn onto floured board and shape into rolls or braids.
Place on slightly greased cookie sheet and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature and then whip till fluffy. Gradually add Eagle Brand milk. Stir until well blended. Add lemon juice and
vanilla and blend well. Pour into crust. Chill 2 -3 hours before garnishing top of pie with cherry pie filling.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Stir together apples and sugar.
Add dry ingredients and stir well.
In separate bowl, beat eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir egg mixture into apple mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cake must spring back when lightly pressed.
Serve with ice cream.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: hershey's chocolate cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 12-inch pan with Pam.
Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs, 1 at a time, and beat well.
Add flour and Hershey's syrup.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cook until knife stuck in middle of cake comes out clean.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Mix and bring to a boil and pour over ribs.
Brown ribs first, about 3 pounds.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine all in crock-pot.
Cook on low 5 to 6 hours.
Discard cinnamon sticks and cloves.
Serve.

title: mission trip oatmeal cookies
directions: Adjust oven racks to low and middle positions and preheat oven to 350°.
Line two large cookie sheets with parchment or foil.
I spray foil with cooking spray.
Whisk flour, salt, baking powder and spices together in medium bowl.
Either by hand
or with electric mixer, beat butter until creamy.
Add sugars, beat until fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Stir dry ingredients into butter-sugar mixture with wooden spoon or large rubber spatula.
Stir in oats and ginger (optional).
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls to cookie sheet.
Bake 10-12 minutes (check at 10 for chewy, a little longer for crisp).
Slide cookies off parchment to cooling rack.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil until quite thick the dates, sugar, butter and egg.
Stir so it does not stick.
Cool a little, then mix with Rice Krispies, or more.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut.
Put on waxed paper to cool.
You can spread in pan and cut into squares also.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry-apple pie
directions: Combine apples and water in a large saucepan. Place over medium heat and cook, uncovered, until apples are slightly soft, about 5 to 8 minutes. Preheat oven to 425°. Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt and blend thoroughly into apples. Add cranberries, orange peel and butter. Cook, uncovered, over medium heat until cranberries start to "pop", about 5 minutes. Spoon into pie shell; top with lattice crust and bake 20 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until top is a deep golden brown, about 25 minutes. Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: surprise salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in small saucepan.
Bring to boil. As soon as it boils, set off stove and let cool for 15 minutes. In large bowl, mix together Cool Whip and buttermilk (surprise!). Pour in jello mixture and stir good.
Chill.

title: chunky chicken vegetable soup
directions: Boil chicken in about 4 cups water; remove skin.
Debone the chicken.
Cook potato or rice and bouillon in chicken stock.

title: marinated chicken breast
directions: Marinate chicken in Pfeiffer Italian (no spices in it) overnight (or at least for 1 hour).
Put chicken breasts with the dressing in a Ziploc bag.
Flip bag over occasionally.

title: pork roast
directions: Marinate in fruit cocktail for 6 hours.
Put apple slices over roast.
Mix remaining ingredients together; simmer over low heat until liquified.
Pour all ingredients over roast.
Bake in a 325° preheated oven, covered, 3 1/2 hours for 5 pound roast or 4 hours for 6 pound roast.

title: finger paint
directions: Put in a double boiler and cook until thick.
Beat with eggbeater and divide into 3 parts.
Tint with food coloring.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup until it boils.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and vanilla; stir until dissolved.
Add cornflakes; stir.
Dip quickly by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: hamburger pinwheels
directions: Fry onion in fat in covered saucepan for 5 minutes.
Mix 2 tablespoons onion with all ingredients, except biscuit dough. Prepare biscuit mix; add remaining onion to biscuit flour.
Roll dough into 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread with meat mixture.
Form in to a log.
Wet edges to seal.
Cut into 12 slices.
Place, cut side up, on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes. Yield:
6 servings.

title: poor man's beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except sour cream and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Blend in sour cream; salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over wide noodles cooked according to package directions.
Quick and delicious!

title: lancaster corn chowder
directions: In a large stockpot, saute onion in butter until tender, but not browned.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour. Adjust seasonings.
Bring to a rapid boil and add Granny's Rolled Dumplings.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes or until dumplings are done.
Serve with cornbread.

title: hershey cocoa fudge
directions: Bring to a boil on high heat, stirring continually, all ingredients except the butter and vanilla.
Reduce to medium heat. Continue to boil, without stirring.
Done when forms soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Set pan in cold water and beat.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Layer broccoli on bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until chicken is fully cooked.

title: fruit and cool whip salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.
Bananas may be added just before serving.

title: low-fat cajun wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Scrub potatoes under running water with soft vegetable brush; rinse.
Dry well.
(Do not peel).
Line baking sheet with aluminum foil and spray with nonstick cooking spray.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise, then cut each half lengthwise into 3 wedges.
Place potatoes, skin sides down, in single layer on prepared baking sheet.
Spray potatoes lightly with cooking spray and sprinkle with seasoning.
Bake 25 minutes or until browned and fork-tender.
Garnish as desired.
Serve immediately.

title: banana blueberry pie
directions: Line crust with bananas (sliced).
Cream together the sugar, cream cheese and lemon juice.
Fold into Cool Whip.
Spread over bananas and top with blueberry pie filling.
Chill.

title: barbecued sausages
directions: Cut Polish sausage or smoked sausages into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces. Split halfway through.
Stuff with sauerkraut. Secure with toothpicks. Place in baking dish. Cover with barbecue sauce. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese and cream with oleo.
Sift other ingredients and add to cheese.
Add cold water and mix well.
Form into a ball with fingers and put in cookie press.
Using the jagged, 1-inch plate, push mixture onto ungreased baking sheet.
If mixture is too stiff, add a little more cold water into press.
Each cheese straw should be about 3-inches long.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove at once to cooling rack.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add mushrooms if you like.
You can always use this sauce for lasagna, too.
Serves 4-6 people.

title: potato wedges
directions: Clean potatoes, leaving skin on. Cut into about 8 wedges each. Mix all ingredients together and dip each wedge into mixture. (May sprinkle with Season-All, if desired.) Lay in shallow pan and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: dorothy's punch
directions: Mix all juices except frozen orange juice and refrigerate. To serve, pour mixed juices into punch bowl and add frozen orange juice.
Float orange slices on top.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bake pie shell 6 minutes in 400° oven.	Combine egg yolks, milk, cornstarch, sugar and chocolate chips.
Microwave 3 minutes. Whisk again and cook another 2 minutes.
Whisk and put in until thick, probably another 2 minutes.	Add butter and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell and cool.
Add whipped topping.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and put into a 10-inch pie pan. Layer remaining ingredients on top as they are listed above.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Mix together eggs, syrup,
sugar,
pumpkin,
salt
and vanilla. Stir in butter and pecans.
Pour
into
unbaked
pie shell and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until set in center.

title: beef roll
directions: Place the flank steak on a board and pound it to tenderize. Crush the garlic and place it on the meat.
Add the olive oil and rub the garlic and oil into the meat.
Arrange the eggs on the meat.
Add the cheeses.
Roll up in a jelly roll style.
Brown in some oil.
Add tomato sauce and bake in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
May use bacon and sliced dill pickles or ham and cheese instead of eggs.

title: red beans and rice(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: In large skillet, saute onions, green peppers and garlic in margarine until onion is tender.
Stir in beans, sausage and bay leaf.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve bean mixture over rice.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Stir together sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla in a 1 1/2 quart dish.
Top
with
butter.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes. Stir smooth.
Blend
in
nuts.
Pour
into wax paper lined 8-inch square dish.

title: african chicken curry and rice
directions: Serve about 2 cups of each in separate bowls.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with 1/2 can onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cover with remaining onions and bake 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: chicken casserole with rice
directions: Combine contents of rice and seasoning packet and water in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Season chicken with salt and pepper to taste. Arrange on top of rice mixture.
Bake covered 1 1/4 hours at 375°, until chicken is tender.
Combine soup and milk; saute almonds in butter until slightly brown.
Pour soup mixture and almonds over chicken.
Bake at 375° uncovered until hot and bubbly!

title: shrimp and wild rice
directions: Saute onion, pepper and mushrooms in margarine until soft. Add seasoning, rice, shrimp and cream sauce.
Bake at 350° in buttered casserole dish until heated through.
Serve with salad.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in large grocery sack (regular weight paper, not too thin).
In a microwave bowl, mix together butter, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook in microwave on High for 4 minutes, stirring twice.
Next add vanilla and baking soda.
Stir until foamy.
Pour mixture over the popped corn in the sack.
Shake to mix.
Cook in microwave 1 1/2 minutes and shake; cook in microwave 1 minute and shake; cook in microwave 1/2 minute and shake.
Spread on wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Spread evenly with a wooden spoon.
Let cool and store in an airtight container.
(Tin cans work well.)

title: doughnut holes
directions: Pour oil
in pan.
Let it get hot.
Cut up biscuits and roll them in little balls.
Put biscuits in oil.
Let them cook until they rise.
Take them out.
Let oil evaporate.
Put the biscuits in a large bowl.
Pour your sugar and cinnamon mix on your biscuits.
Let cool and eat.

title: onion dip(cipolla bagna)
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature and mix with the rest of the ingredients.
Beat
well.
Serve
with
fresh
cut vegetables or chips.

title: honeyed chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in skillet; add honey, mustard and curry powder.
Pour into a large shallow pan.
Roll chicken pieces in mixture to cover all sides.
Leave skin side down.
Bake 45 minutes, basting often.
Turn and bake 15 minutes more.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the 1 cup sugar, flour or cornstarch and salt; gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Stir 1 cup of hot mixture into the beaten egg yolks.
Immediately return all mixture to hot mixture in the saucepan.
Return to gentle boil.
Cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter or margarine and 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 teaspoon coconut.
Stir in 1 cup coconut.
Pour into cooled baked pie shell.

title: pudding(diet)
directions: Add 1/2 box cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Add milk; mix well.
Add package of pudding to mixture.
Beat well.
Pour into serving dishes.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top.
Serves 4.

title: hot chile
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Drain off all fat.
Put in crock-pot; add tomato paste, tomato juice, tomatoes, soup beans (wash and drain beans good), chile powder, red pepper and salt. Cook all day on low.

title: meatballs in onion soup
directions: Mix ground meat, eggs, and bread crumbs and season.
Shape into balls,
Combine soup, cornstarch, and water
in a large bowl and microwave for 5 minutes.
Add meatballs to gravy and bake in a 350 degree oven for 1-1/2 hours.

title: hamburger soup
directions: First, use care and get one, not too young, but tender and a healthy growth.
Make your selection carefully and let it be final. Otherwise, they will not keep.
Like fine wine, they improve with age.
Do not pickle or put in hot water.
This makes them sour. Prepare as follows; sweeten with smiles.
The sour bitter kind are improved by a pinch of common sense.
Spice with patience.
Wrap well in a mantle of love.
Preserve over a good fire of steady devotion.
The poorest varieties may be improved by this process and kept years in any climate.

title: chinese sesame seed chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs, corn flakes, sesame seed and seasonings. Dip chicken in buttermilk then into crumb mixture, coating both sides.
Heat oil in large skillet. Brown chicken on both sides. Dip in Teriyaki sauce made from 1/2 cup teriyaki sauce and 1 Tbsp. corn starch, heated till thickened.

title: chocolate cake with its icing
directions: Cook pudding as to directions on box.
Add chocolate cake mix. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and chopped nuts on top of batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: make ahead dried beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook the noodles and mix with the chopped vegetables.

title: salmon salad
directions: Tomato Salad:
Stuff small tomato with cottage cheese and chives.

title: homemade beef soup
directions: Cook 1 hour or more or more.
Add cream if desired.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thick. Stir margarine and cheese into grits and mix well. Break eggs into measuring cup and add milk to make 1 cup. Stir into grits mixture and mix well. Put into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: apple oatmeal crisp
directions: This formula for making as much or as little chocolate pudding as you want is very easy.
Also good for filling eclairs.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Measure flour into bowl; make a well in center and add egg yolks, whole egg and salt.
Thoroughly mix into flour.
Add water, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Form dough into a ball.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts.
Roll dough 1 part at a time into paper-thin rectangle.
Cut dough crosswise into 1/8-inch strips for narrow noodles and place on towel to dry about 2 hours.
When dry, break into smaller strips.
Cook in 3 quarts water or broth.
Add cooked chicken or any kind of meat.

title: apple pie
directions: In large bowl, blend flour, butter, vegetable shortening and salt until mixture resembles meal.
Add 2 tablespoons ice water; toss mixture until water is incorporated, adding the additional ice water if necessary to form a dough.
Form dough into a ball. Dust the dough with flour and chill it, wrapped in wax paper, for 1 hour.
Make 2 of these for one pie.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix butter, flour, milk, Cheez Whiz and cream of mushroom soup.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
(Add Cheez Whiz last.)
Crumble crackers in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer with 1/2 can of asparagus and 1/2 can of peas, then cheese mixture. Repeat, ending with cheese mixture.
Crumble crackers on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: In blender or food processor, combine all ingredients until smooth.
Store up to one week in refrigerator.
This recipe substitutes for one 14-ounce can.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix together and chill well before serving.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and cocoa well.
Add flour and eggs.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: 1 & 1 baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion; drain fat.
Set aside. Drain all three cans of beans and mix with first mixture.
Add sugar and barbecue sauce and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon chicken breasts
directions: Heat oil in a heavy skillet until hot; add chicken and cook 5 minutes in each side.
Place chicken in an 8-inch square baking dish; discard drippings.
Add parsley flakes and next 3 ingredients to skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with lemon juice, pepper and paprika.
Cover and bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until tender.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt margarine and semi-sweet chocolate chips over low heat until melted.
In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool for 2 to 3 hours.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add pineapple with juice and frozen strawberries with juice, nuts, bananas and Cool Whip.
Mix well and freeze.

title: toasted aromatic pecans
directions: Put pecans on a 13 x 9 baking sheet.
Toast in a preheated 300° oven for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt butter, add Bitters and 1 teaspoon seasoning salt.
Pour mixture over pecans and stir; coating pecans evenly.
Cook for 15 minutes longer.
Add more seasoning salt if desired.
Remove; spread out on paper towels to dry.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Shake all ingredients well in large container.
Pour into freezable containers and freeze.
Serves 12.

title: pecan pie ii
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, syrup and salt.
Mix well.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat.
Pour pecans in pie shell.
Pour in mixture over nuts.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes.
Then 300 degrees for 35 minutes longer.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, vanilla, oil and zucchini.
Stir dry ingredients together, and then add to the wet mixture.
Add nuts and blend well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 greased bread pans.

title: party salad
directions: Dissolve jello and marshmallows in the 2 cups of boiling water.
Mix cream cheese and mayo well.
Add to jello and marshmallow mixture.
Blend with electric mixture until smooth. Let cool and then add crushed pineapple, whipping cream and chopped nuts.
Pour in salad and congeal in refrigerator. Decorate with maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and then add cornbread mix last. Bake in a 7x
11-inch greased pan or in muffin pans.
Best when hot.
Serves 18.

title: sugar-free pie filling
directions: Beat until stiff Dream Whip and cold milk.
Add sugar-free pudding and cold milk.
Beat until fluffy.
Pour into pie crust.

title: true-blue potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss the potatoes, onions and celery. In a small bowl, combine the sour cream, mayonnaise, parsley, vinegar, salt, pepper and celery seed. Pour over potato mixture; toss to coat. Sprinkle with Blue cheese. Cover and refrigerate for several hours before serving. Yield: 8 servings.

title: raw spinach salad
directions: Grind spinach, then measure.
Add onion, celery, eggs, salt and mayonnaise.
Toss lightly.
Add vinegar and Tabasco just before serving.

title: kathy levine's sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken, in T-Fal wok.
Mix in separate saucepan brown sugar, vinegar, lemon juice, soy sauce, cornstarch.
Cook until thickened.
Add pineapple juice and enough water to make one quart; stir, add pineapple.
Add mushrooms, green peppers, onions to mixture.
Add the mixture to the chicken in ovenware baking pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lena's fruit salad
directions: Add all fruits together.
