Drain pineapple (save juice).
Mix vanilla pudding with pineapple juice.
Pour over fruit and refrigerate overnight.
Great for diabetics.
No sugar.
No fat.

title: pumpkin ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt cake pan.

title: roasted broccoli with sesame dressing
directions: In a bowl, toss the broccoli with the olive oil until it is coated well and roast in a preheated 500° oven, turning occasionally with tongs, for 10 to 12 minutes or until it is crisp-tender.
While the broccoli is roasting, in a blender, blend the lemon juice, oils, soy sauce, seed, ginger, garlic and sugar until smooth.
Transfer broccoli to serving dish and pour dressing over it.

title: dirt
directions: Crush Oreos.
Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Add milk, pudding and Cool Whip to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Line 8-inch flowerpot with plastic wrap to cover holes.
Alternate 1-inch layer of crumbs and filling, ending with crumbs. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Decorate with flowers, shovels or gummy worms.

title: beverly's cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and corn syrup together and boil for 1 minute, stirring continuously.
Remove from heat and then stir in peanut butter, then add Corn Flakes at a time.
Drop by spoonful on aluminum foil or wax paper.
Let set for about 5 minutes. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: barbecue
directions: Hamburger:
Brown hamburger and onion; drain excess grease. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add yolks, juice and rind.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with water.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in either 9 x 13-inch pan or two 9-inch layer pans for 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: pink lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice and food coloring.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour into pie plate lined with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Place in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours before serving. Makes 2 pies.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown meat, pepper, onion, oregano, salt and pepper.
Drain all grease.
Add tomato paste and sauce.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add cottage cheese and mix well.
Place layer of noodles in bottom of dish.
Add meat mixture and layer of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dried beef canapes
directions: Cook onion in butter till tender; add dried beef and cook till beef is slightly crisp. Add beef mixture to the cream cheese. Blend. Spread on saltines or crisp rye wafers.

title: italian salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Cut cheese, salami, pepperoni and peppers into strips.
Cut tomatoes into wedges.
Toss all ingredients together except oil and vinegar.
Refrigerate until ready serve.
Combine oil and vinegar.
Pour over salad; mix and serve.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: racy red punch
directions: Heat 1 cup of drink with candies, stirring constantly for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and add to rest of drink.
Chill. Combine with ginger ale just before serving.

title: chicken strip supper
directions: Cook chicken strips; drain grease and remove chicken.
Add cream of chicken soup and add enough water to make gravy.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put chicken back in skillet and simmer.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
(No eggs needed.)

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in hard boiling water until almost done. Drain and layer in well-buttered casserole dish. Add chicken pieces and the prepared stuffing (recipe on box). Layer broccoli, chicken and stuffing until stuffing is on top.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in Bundt or loaf pan at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ziti noodles
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion in skillet.
Drain fat.
Cook noodles according to package.
Layer ingredients: cooked noodles, hamburger, onion, spaghetti sauce, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and 1 cup Cheddar cheese; repeat.

title: no peek beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 2-quart baking dish and cook, covered, for 2 hours at 325°.
Serve over rice or noodles; this can also be cooked in crock-pot.

title: r v pate
directions: Mash all together.
Serve with crackers or dark bread.

title: squash casserole supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Cut up squash. Cook until tender. Drain thoroughly and mash well. Chop onion.

title: impossible chili pie
directions: Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate; brown meat.
Drain; add tomatoes, onion and seasonings.
Spread in plate; sprinkle with olives and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients in gradually until smooth and pour into dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: snow cream
directions: Mix all together and add snow until thick.

title: frozen bananas
directions: Line a large baking sheet with waxed paper.
Combine butter and chocolate chips in a small skillet or pan.
Stir over low heat until melted.
Stir in milk. Cut bananas in half and dip in chocolate.
Dip in nuts before chocolate sets. Freeze until firm, about 1 hour.
Put in freezer bags.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: meatballs
directions: Can add small pieces of pepperoni for an extra zip!!

title: spaghetti for 60
directions: Combine and bring to a boil.
Simmer until thick.

title: chocolate date nut cake
directions: In a bowl, combine boiling water, dates and baking soda; mix well and set aside.
Sift flour, baking soda (1 teaspoon), salt and cocoa.
In mixer, beat butter and 1 cup sugar until smooth. Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well.
Add date mixture; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over batter.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; cover with chocolate chips and walnuts.
Return to oven for 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting. Refrigerate leftovers.
This recipe is from "Death By Chocolate" and probably would be if eaten very often.
Delicious!

title: sausage and cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Separate crescent dough into 2 large rectangles.
Place in ungreased baker.
Press over bottom and halfway up sides to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Crumb sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Mix remaining ingredients; add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moist. Fill muffin tins, greased.
Bake until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° in 3 cake pans for 15 to 20 minutes.
Layers are very thin.
Let cool in pan.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening, peanut butter and all sugars until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Add to flour; mix well.
Form in small balls; place 1 inch apart.
Press crosswise with fork.
Bake 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet at 350°.

title: meuseli
directions: Toast oats on cookie sheet in a 250° oven for 2 hours.
Put first 3 ingredients into a bowl; cover and let soak overnight.
In the morning, serve with grated apples, coconut or almonds on top. Meuseli will be sweeter if allowed to soak 2 to 3 days in the refrigerator.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients. Shape into ball. Roll in chopped nuts. Refrigerate and serve with crackers.

title: chicken with orange sauce
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Season chicken breast with salt, ginger and pepper; place in pan (9 x 11-inch) and set aside.
Combine the chicken stock, orange juice, honey and lemon juice and bring to boil, thicken slightly with 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Spoon sauce over and under chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° until tender, turning once (45 to 55 minutes).
Serve over rice pilaf. (Can freeze, defrost overnight in refrigerator and reheat, covered, at 325°.)

title: frozen strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in the boiling water.
Add all the remaining ingredients except for the ginger ale.
Pour into 2 one-gallon interlock plastic bags and freeze until needed.
One and one-half hours before needed, thaw slightly.
Work the mixture with your hands into a fine ice.
Pour into a punch bowl and add the ginger ale.
Stir.

title: banana split cake(a weight watcher recipe)
directions: Mix the graham crackers and melted margarine and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice
the bananas on top of the crust. Spread in layers on top
of
bananas, the banana pudding, then the drained pineapple.
Top it
with
the
Cool
Whip
and the sliced strawberries.
Chill.
Not
bad
Weight Watchers!!
You would count it like
this:
fruit, 1 bread, 1 fat, 1/2 meat and 50 optional calories.
Makes 8 servings.

title: nellie's barbecue sauce
directions: Saute greens in butter, then add the rest of ingredients. Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: old fashioned walnut balls
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Sift flour and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: tomato salad
directions: Mix together.
May not sound like much but it will disappear.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef; add Ro-Tel, tomatoes, taco mix and dressing mix; stir well and let simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add beans and corn; continue to stir until warm through. Serve in soup bowls; drop a spoon of sour cream in center and sprinkle with cheese.

title: chocolate oat granola bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, sugar, margarine and mix well.
Reserve 1/2 cup.
Press remaining mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove and pour milk over top. Sprinkle with nuts and chips.
Top with reserved oats.
Press lightly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: fried okra
directions: Soak okra in eggs. Mix cornmeal, salt, and pepper. Heat oil. dip okra in cornmeal. Coat evenly, then place in hot oil. Cook until golden brown.

title: esther's tamale pie
directions: Saute meat and drain well.
Set aside in large bowl or pan. Saute onion and pepper.
Add this and all other ingredients to meat.
Mix really well. Put in casserole dish and bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients in mixing bowl and beat with mixer until blended.
Pour into crusts and freeze overnight,
at least 24 hours.
Yields 2 pies.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown together meat, onion and garlic.
Add the other ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: holiday potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in water until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add butter and cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 cup cheese and next 6 ingredients.
Spoon in greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese and bake 5 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Put chicken (or parts; I use breasts for company) in water to cover and cook until tender.
Remove chicken skin and bones and cut up.
Place celery and onions in a pan with a little oleo, as for dressing.
Cook until tender; mix with chicken and place in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour oleo over chicken.
Combine soup and broth and pour over chicken.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and milk and pour over chicken mixture (this rises and makes the crust).
Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes (check pie at 35 minutes).
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of chicken soup

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Cook apples and apple juice together in saucepan until apples are tender (hot through).
Mix cornstarch and cinnamon.
Add about 1/4 cup cold water.
Add this to hot apple mixture.
Put filling in pie shell.
Add top pastry strips.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: strawberries with chocolate cream
directions: Beat whipping cream until foamy.
Sift cocoa and powdered sugar together.
Serve with strawberries.
Yield: about 6 1/2 dozen appetizers.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Beat egg in 1 tablespoon of water; roll chicken in egg mixture, then tumble in crumbs.
Brown chicken in shortening; pour off fat.
Stir in soup, 1/4 cup water, onion and seasonings.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll out dough into an oblong shape.
Spread with butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up tightly.
Pinch edges.
Stretch slightly to even.
Cut into 1-inch slices and place into greased pan.
Cover and let rise until doubled (35 to 40 minutes).
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
After rolls have cooled, add your favorite topping (icing, brown sugar, peanut butter, raisins, etc.).

title: kirk's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Put barbecue sauce in large pot.
Add brown sugar and about 3/4 can of beer to sauce and cook on low heat.
Put ground meat in a bowl.
Then add egg and bread crumbs and mix.
Break stems of mushrooms and stuff meat inside each one, then put them in barbecue sauce and cook about 2 1/2 hours or in crock-pot overnight on low.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans together; spread into baking dish or pan (9 x 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool completely.

title: moon cake
directions: Stir until thick.
Slice angel food cake into 9 x 12-inch pan. Add 8 ounces sour cream to pudding mixture.
Add 20 ounce can crushed pineapple (drain all but 1/4 cup).
Stir.
Layer pudding and cake mixture until all is used.
Refrigerate 1 hour and serve.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip together with a spoon.
Line a 15 x 9 x 2-inch pan with graham crackers.
Pour half of the pudding mixture over crackers.
Repeat.
Top second layer with crackers.
Spread frosting over top layer of crackers.
Garnish with cherries.
Chill.

title: special corn bread
directions: Rub inside of a 9-inch layer pan with garlic; grease pan well. Add milk, egg, onion and oil to combined dry ingredients; mix until well blended.
Pour into prepared 9-inch layer pan and bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan; cut into wedges.
Serve warm with butter.
Makes 9-inch round corn bread.

title: filled fudge cake
directions: Melt chocolate. Cool. Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt into large bowl. Beat in sour cream and margarine; beat in eggs, one at a time. Blend almond extract, hot water and chocolate. Pour into greased and floured cake pans. Cook at 350° until done.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in two round 8 or 9-inch pans.
Cool.
Place one cake in bottom of a trifle dish. Poke holes in top of cake with a fork.
Pour Kahlua (according to taste preference) over cake.
Make pudding and pour half over cake. Layer 1/2 Cool Whip.
Sprinkle 1/2 crushed candy bars over Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.

title: impossible pie(coconut or pineapple)
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, milk, vanilla, melted oleo and coconut or pineapple.
Pour into well-greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This pie makes its own crust.
Make sure it is cool before slicing.

title: simple chicken spaghetti
directions: Simmer leg quarters until tender.
Remove chicken from broth and cool.
Reserve 1 cup broth.
Place spaghetti in cup of broth and boil (do not drain).
When chicken has cooled, cut into small pieces.
Add chicken to cooked spaghetti.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix with chicken-spaghetti.
Place in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes (less time if using microwave). Should serve 4 to 6 people, depending on who is eating it!

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar, flour and pineapple juice.
Add to pineapple and cheese.
Cover with crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken balls
directions: Mix all together. Shape into 1-inch balls. Refrigerate and before serving, roll into chopped walnuts.

title: microwave applesauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a 2-quart microwave-safe baking dish. Cover and cook on High for 6 to 8 minutes.
Using a food processor, process until smooth.
Makes 8 1/2 cups.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours or until serving time.
Yields about 1 1/2 cups.

title: pickled beets
directions: Wash beets,
leaving on root and 1 inch of tops.
Cover beets with
water,
bring
to
boil, then simmer until tender. Drain; slip off skins and trim beets.
In large kettle combine vinegar, water,
sugar and spices and bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes. Add beets and simmer for an additional 5 minutes. Pack beets
in hot jars and cover with boiling syrup, leaving 1/2
inch headspace.
Adjust
lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 30 minutes.

title: blender egg pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
(If electric mixer is used, add one ingredient at a time.)
Put into pie pan.
Let set about 5 minutes.
Then bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven even if shaky.
It will finish cooking.
Makes its own crust.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Salt chicken lightly.
Grease large baking pan.
On each chicken breast, place 1/2 strip of bacon and 1 piece of chipped beef.
Combine sour cream, mushroom soup and a little water.
Pour over chicken.
Cover; bake at 250° for 3 hours, then remove cover and bake 1 more hour.

title: andrea's waffles
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites until stiff.
Combine egg yolks, flour, baking powder, salt, milk and oil.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake on waffle iron.
Also makes good Belgian waffles.

title: macaroon ice cream pie
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add salt, vanilla and sugar and blend well.
Combine baking powder, graham cracker crumbs, chopped walnuts and coconut, then fold into egg white mixture.
Pour ingredients into a 9-inch pie pan (glass preferred) with high edges.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Excellent served with strawberries, vanilla ice cream and/or Grand Marnier.

title: far east celery
directions: Cut celery into 1-inch pieces and cook until tender but crisp (8
minutes).
Put
into
a
1 quart casserole.
Stir in water chestnuts,
cream
of
chicken
soup
and pimento.
Mix lightly bread crumbs, almonds and butter and sprinkle over the casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute in large pot the bacon and minced onion. Then add potatoes, 1 cup water, celery and carrots. Cook until tender. Just before serving, add 2 cups milk, salt, pepper and creamed corn. Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Serve immediately. Makes 6 servings.

title: steamed carrots with parsley
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 15 minutes or until carrots are tender when pricked with a fork.
Drain and serve.

title: lasagna deluxe
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil the noodles in a large pot.
Be sure not to overcook them. (They are done when they are soft.)

title: hobo dinners
directions: Take aluminum foil.
Butter one side.
Place ingredients on foil.
Fold foil.
Crimp two sides.
Add 1 tablespoon water. Crimp and seal remaining side.
Place on grill, camp fire or oven. Cook for about 1/2 hour.
Turn over.
Cook for another 1/2 hour. Open foil and eat.
(Cooking times may vary.)

title: orange congealed salad(9 x 13-inch)
directions: Boil crushed pineapple and sugar.
Add Jell-O and cold water. Refrigerate until partially set.
Add grated cheese, Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll dough very thin.
Cut in squares.
Drop in boiling chicken stock.

title: stir and pat biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and soda in small bowl.
Pour oil and buttermilk into a measuring cup.
Do not stir.
Add all at once to flour mixture and stir until mixture cleans sides of bowl and mounds into a ball.
Pinch off walnut-sized ball and pat out flat onto greased pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 475°.
Makes 15 biscuits.

title: cherries crunch
directions: Press in pan.
Spray with Pam.
Bake until looks brown or 20 or 30 minutes.

title: *hot german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon over low heat until crisp; drain and crumble.
Add celery and onion to 1/4 cup drippings and saute until tender. Combine sugar, flour and seasonings.
Stir into the drippings. Add water and vinegar; stir until smooth.
Bring to a boil and add potatoes and bacon.
Toss.
Serves 6.

title: italian baked eggplant
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Dip sliced eggplant into egg-milk mixture. Dredge in bread crumbs.
Brown in a frypan with vegetable oil. Place browned eggplant slices into oven-proof dish.
Top with sliced cheese.
Pour spaghetti sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: no cook - pineapple frosting for 9 x 13-inch cake
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding; fold in Cool Whip.

title: veggie dip
directions: Beat together with mixer until creamy.
Store in refrigerator.

title: tofu burgers
directions: Mix together well.
Shape into patties.
Fry in a small amount of oil (divide for small family).

title: zehnder's pecan pie
directions: Whip the eggs and blend in sugar, syrup, vanilla and salt.
Add melted butter and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared crust. Bake at 375° to 400° for 45 to 60 minutes or until slightly puffy.

title: mrs. l. baggett's pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and cream again.
Add egg yolks, then add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Add flavoring.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/4 hours, or until tested done.

title: cheese and broccoli soup
directions: In a large saucepan, add broccoli, chicken broth, onion and pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat to low and cover and simmer for approximately 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Process in blender until smooth and return to pan.
Add all but 1/4 cup of the milk.
Return to boil, stirring occasionally.
Stir the cornstarch into the reserved 1/4 cup milk until smooth.
Add slowly to boiling soup mixture.
Simmer until thickened (about 1 minute).
Reduce heat and stir in cheese pieces until melted. Makes about 7 cups.

title: poor man's eggs benedict
directions: Prepare cheese soup according to directions on can but cut back on milk by at least half (or too taste) to make a cheese sauce.
Toast English muffins, fry sausage (four 3 ounce patties), and poach eggs.
Place sausage patties on English muffins.
Place poached egg on top of sausage.
Pour cheese sauce over all. Sprinkle with dash of paprika.
Garnish with parsley.
This is an artery plugger, but it tastes great!

title: corned beef barbados
directions: Saute onion in butter for 2 minutes.
Add corned beef and cook another 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, curry, salt and pepper; simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Cook amount of rice desired.
Make long cooking rice according to box directions except add onion and thyme.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix and bake for 1 hour at 300° in greased, oblong pan.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground meat with onion. Salt and pepper to taste.

Add cream of mushroom soup and mix up; simmer. Fix mashed potatoes according to package on box. Pour ground meat mixture into deep casserole dish. Pour drained corn on top, then place mashed potatoes on top of corn. Spread grated cheese on top of mashed potatoes. Bake in oven for approximately 30 to 35 minutes at about 300°. Watch that cheese doesn't burn.

title: rice casserole
directions: Fry bacon until almost crispy; drain grease.
Add onion and bell pepper and fry until soft.
In casserole dish, add beef consomme, water, sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Add bacon, onion, bell pepper and rice; stir.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until rice is done.
Bacon and bell pepper will rise to the top.

title: rice with chicken and beans(spanish)
directions: Put 1 tablespoon corn oil in a pot.
Put the cut up pieces of chicken with Adobo and salt in the pot.
Add 2 envelopes of sazon seasoning.
Add garlic and onion powder.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Then add 2 cups of rice to the pot with the chicken. Add 2 1/2 cups of water.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix well and bake at 375°.

title: grilled sirloin steak
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the first seven ingredients; add beef.
Seal bag and turn to coat; refrigerate for at least 3 hours or overnight.
Drain and discard the marinade. Grill steak, covered, over indirect medium heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, turning once, or until meat reaches desired doneness.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream
sugar
and shortening together well.
Add margarine and beat
until
fluffy.
Add
egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and buttermilk alternating with sifted flour, salt and soda.
Add coconut and pecans.
Fold in
beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pecos cantaloupe pickles
directions: Select cantaloupes which are not too ripe.
Peel and cut into large cubes.
Cover with mild vinegar and let stand 24 hours. Pour off vinegar, then prepare a syrup of sugar, spices and 1 quart fresh vinegar.
Boil until thick; skim.
Simmer the melon cubes in this syrup 20 minutes.
Lift with perforated skimmer and pack quickly into sterilized jars.
Boil syrup down until thick; pour over fruit in jars and seal.

title: nanaimo bars
directions: Crush graham crackers in a plastic bag with a rolling pin.
Mix together 1 cube butter or margarine, 3/4 cups granulated sugar, 3 eggs, 3 teaspoons vanilla and 2 1/2 tablespoons cocoa.
Set over boiling water and stir until slightly thickened.
Add 1 cup of chopped nuts and 3 cups flaked coconut and graham cracker crumbs. Put into a 12 x 15-inch baking pan and press down evenly and solidly.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix tapioca and orange jello in saucepan with 3 cups boiling water.
Stir well until mixed.
Return mixture to heat and cook until mixture thickens, stirring frequently.
Cool in refrigerator.
Blend in Cool Whip and mandarin oranges and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and refrigerate until thoroughly cooled.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and finish filling the container with milk and freeze.

title: broccoli casserole(serves 12)
directions: Cook broccoli; add all ingredients except 1/2 stick margarine and Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Press bottom and sides of unbaked shell with fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until dry.
Remove to rack.
Put potatoes in medium bowl.
Break up with electric mixer; add sugar and butter.
Beat until well blended and smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread in pans.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 325°.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until pick comes out clean.
Cool in pan or on wire rack.

title: cornmeal biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Stir together flour and cornmeal.
Cut in shortening until mixture looks like meal.
Stir in milk to make soft dough.
Round up on lightly floured board (or wax paper). Knead lightly.
Roll or pat out to 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into biscuit or diamond shapes with floured knife.
Place on ungreased baking sheet, close together for biscuits with soft sides or 1 inch apart for crusty sides.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: apple nut horseradish dip
directions: Blend together and serve with crackers or chips.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Shape into loaf with wet hands.
Dot the top with 1 tablespoon shortening.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Makes 4 servings.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions and drain.
Add tomato soup, peas, salt and pepper.
Put mixture into a 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Cut cheese slices into 3/4-inch cubes and place on top of meat mixture. Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bar balued prawns
directions: Put prawns in a pie plate.
Add oil, garlic, salt and pepper. Broil for 10 minutes.
Place in platter.
Add lemon and serve. Serves 2

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cover and chill.
Good served with Hawaiian bread, pumpernickel bread or assorted crackers.

title: mother's dumplings
directions: Drop into boiling broth (chicken or ham and string beans). Cover (don't lift cover) and cook for 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute crackers in margarine.
Mix drained corns together. Layer corn and crackers.
End with crackers.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: chop suey bars
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut while warm in bars or squares.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 large or 4 medium size bread pans.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together in any order.
Bake 1 hour or until lightly browned.

title: stewed tomato chicken
directions: Place chicken in a microwavable casserole dish.
Add stewed tomatoes.
Microwave, covered, 6 to 10 minutes on High.

title: thai fried noodles
directions: Heat oil in a wok and saute the garlic and pickled radish. Add eggs and stir.
Season with sugar, fish sauce, vinegar and paprika.
Add meat, bean curd and noodles.
Toss and cook for about 10 minutes.
Then add green onions, ground chili, bean sprouts and peanuts.
Remove from heat.
Garnish with additional peanuts if desired and lime on the side.

title: turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Can add frozen peas and pimento.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.
Serves 12.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat until blended well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in jam; fold in egg whites.
Bake in tube pan in 325° oven for 30 minutes. Increase heat to 350° and cook for 45 minutes or until cake is done.
Allow to cool in pan for 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes or heat canned potatoes in syrup until most of the liquid has evaporated.
Beat potatoes with mixer, if available.
Thoroughly mix in margarine, sugar, salt and spices. Add eggs, milk, evaporated milk and vanilla; mix well.
Do not scrape beaters.

title: lazy peach pie
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sift together sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Pour peaches over batter (juice and all).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until browned.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mash up with hands; make ball and roll the ball in crushed pecans.

title: cheddar cheese potatoes
directions: You will need 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: mary jane jones' punch
directions: Mix packages of Kool-Aid as directed; sweeten to taste.
Add pineapple juice.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: pork pies
directions: Put meat and onions in soup pan. Add salt, pepper, cinnamon, cloves and water.
Cook on medium heat. When meat is done cooking, roll out about 1 sleeve of saltine crackers until very fine. Add to meat while still in pan.
Makes about 3 pies.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Fold in strawberries.
Mix pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Add this to gelatin.
Pour into a pan and chill until firm.
Mix the marshmallows with sour cream and Cool Whip.
Spread this mixture at once on top of the firm gelatin mixture.

title: orange julius
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in blender; blend completely.
Add ice and blend on high for 5 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly.
Add vanilla and salt.
Pour boiling water over raisins and let stand a few minutes.
Drain.
Add to creamed shortening mixture.
Dissolve soda in milk and add alternately with flour to creamed shortening mixture.
Add oatmeal.
Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased 10 x 14-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan to cake cooler immediately after baking.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble biscuits and cornbread mix all together. Spray 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: sweet & sour meatballs
directions: Mix ground chuck, crackers, milk, grated onion, salt, and pepper together and form into golf ball size meatballs.

title: filled ice box cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar, add beaten eggs and mix well.
Sift the dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out each half until 1/2 inch thick.
Spread each half with filling mixture and roll as for a jelly roll.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: cinnamon pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil, water, butter flavoring and vanilla flavoring.
While mixing, combine 1/2 cup white sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 1/2 cup nuts.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Sprinkle a thin layer of nuts in bottom of pan.
Pour 1/3 of batter over this.
Sprinkle 1/3 sugar-cinnamon mixture over this. Repeat three times.
Bake at 325°.
Turn out while warm.
Pour over cake: 1 box 10x sugar, 1 teaspoon butter flavoring, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 3 teaspoons of milk.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine ingredients.
Turn into a buttered casserole.
Dot with butter and cook at 400° about 25 minutes.
Cover with marshmallows and brown.

title: bread sticks
directions: Mix well the oleo and seasoning and spread on all cut sides of bread.
Cut buns into strips, 3 to the top and 2 to the bottom. Bake at 250° for 2 hours or until dry and slightly brown.

title: green noodles
directions: Wash spinach.

Place into a heavy saucepan. Do not add water. Cook only in the moisture remaining on the leaves from washing. Partially cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally with a fork. Drain spinach, pressing out water and chop finely.
Mix flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a bowl,
making a well in center. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing slightly after each addition. Add the chopped spinach and mix well.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth, adding flour if needed to make a stiff dough.
Divide dough in half.
Lightly roll each half into a rectangle, about 1/8-inch thick. Cover and let stand for 1 hour.

title: lazy peach pie
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix with milk and pour into pan.
Pour canned peaches with syrup over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until golden brown.
Use cherries or apricots with great results.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together well.
(You'll have to use your hands.) Sprinkle with a little water while mixing to make better consistency for rolling into balls.
Roll into small balls.
Bake for 30 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet in a 350° oven.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Chop broccoli and lightly cook.
Melt butter; add onion and stir in flour.
Add milk to make gravy.
Add cream of mushroom or chicken soup; add the broccoli.
Add the Cheddar cheese soup and cook until cheese is melted.

title: popover pizza
directions: Cook ground chuck and onion in a large skillet until browned; drain.
Add sauce mix, tomato sauce and water, mixing well. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Spoon meat into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Beat eggs, milk and oil until foamy.
Add flour and salt; beat until smooth.
Pour batter over meat mixture, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, or until top is puffed and golden brown.
Serve hot.
Yields 8 servings.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix mayo, cheeses and artichokes in medium casserole.
Grate fresh pepper over top.
Bake, uncovered, for about 1/2 hour or until spread is bubbly and brown around the edges.
Spread on slices of French bread.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Slice pepperoni and Mozzarella thin.
Put to the side.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Prepare pastry for 9-inch two-crust pie. Mix as directed on package.
Mix peaches and lemon juice. Stir together sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Mix with peaches.
Turn into pastry lined pie pan. Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust which has slits cut in it.
Seal and flute.
Cover edge with 2 to 3-inch strip of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning.
Remove foil the last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Prepare cake mix as directed, adding 1/3 cup margarine and 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 of batter into pan and bake for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Add 1/2 cup evaporated milk to melted caramels and pour over baked cake.
Spread over this the package of chocolate chips, then the cup of nuts.
Add remaining batter. Return to oven and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
"Out of this world."

title: the giant's spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients, blend well.
Cover; refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with crisp vegetable dippers.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Blend milk and eggs mixture and dry ingredients.
Add melted fat.
Cook in skillet until golden brown or done.

title: tomato sauce jambalaya
directions: Fry sausage and cubed meat until slightly brown in a large heavy saucepan.
Add onion, peppers and garlic.
Brown slightly. Add water, tomato sauce, chicken broth, seasoning, bouillon and meat.
Simmer on medium heat for 45 minutes.
Add rice and cook, covered, on low heat until rice is done.
(Too much stirring will make sticky.)

title: chocolate chip raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: *Or 1/2 of each.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Cream the powdered sugar and oleo together.
Add beaten egg, salt and vanilla; mix until light and fluffy.
Spoon mixture evenly into the 2 pie shells; chill.

title: onion buttered julienne vegies
directions: Saute carrots and celery in onion butter in large skillet over medium heat three minutes.
Stir in zucchini;
cook covered over low heat until veggies are crisp tender, about 3 minutes longer.

title: hot crab melts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine crabmeat, sauce, celery, green pepper and lemon juice (if desired).
Spread equal amounts on muffin halves.
Bake 5 minutes.
Top each with cheese slice.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until hot.
Serve immediately. Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 4.

title: creamy surprise gelatin salad
directions: Heat fruit cocktail on stove for a few minutes; add pineapple. Stir cream cheese into jello, fruit cocktail and pineapple until smooth.
When jello is part thickened, fold in Dream Whip and fresh strawberries.
If dark cherry jello is used, use fresh Bing cherries.
If orange jello is used, use mandarin oranges.
If peach jello, use fresh peaches.

title: jewel salad
directions: Mix lemon Jell-O as directed on box, reducing water by 1/4 cup.
Pour into bowl and chill until slightly thickened, but not set.
Whip Dream Whip with milk until fluffy, then fold into slightly thickened lemon Jell-O.
Cut pans of Jell-O into squares; fold into lemon mixture (reserving a few of each color).
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan; top with reserved pieces and chill until firm.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: carrot ice cream pie
directions: In small bowl combine graham cracker crumbs and brown sugar; stir in butter.
Press onto bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, place lemonade concentrate, carrots and sugar in food processor or blender; cover and process until carrots are finely chopped and mixture is blended.
Transfer to a bowl and stir in ice cream until well blended.
Pour into crust; cover and freeze for 8 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer 15-20 minutes before serving. Yield:
6-8 servings.

title: microwave cake
directions: For a refreshing dessert, ready in a flash, try a yellow microwave cake mix with sliced bananas and a glaze of apricot preserves.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Melt red hot candy and water over medium heat, stirring constantly, until all is melted. Add apples and stir until evenly coated. Simmer about 30 minutes, or until apples are soft. Serve hot.

title: quick doughnuts
directions: Blend eggs until thick and lemon color.
Gradually beat in sugar and nutmeg.
Blend in shortening and flour, mixing in with milk.
Use enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board; mix gently for 30 seconds, until 1/2-inch thick. Cut with floured doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep fat at 400° for 1 1/2 minutes, or until brown on each side.
Drain well.
While warm, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: natural applesauce cake
directions: Spray desired size pans with cooking spray.
Prepare cake mix according to directions with the following modifications:
Add 1 tablespoon flour to the dry mix.
Stir well.
Substitute an equal amount of Mott's natural applesauce for the vegetable oil.
Bake and cool as directed.
Frost cake with your choice of frosting. Garnish with fresh berries, if desired.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix with hands; form into balls.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan; boil.
Pour syrup over berries and chill.
If frozen berries are used, use the syrup to make 1 3/4 cups liquid.
If berries are sweetened, use only 1 cup sugar.

title: scalloped corn and oysters
directions: Combine corn, beaten egg, milk, salt and pepper; add crushed crackers and mix.
Fold in oysters.
Place in a baking dish; dot with butter or margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
(Does not have a strong oyster taste.)

title: beef bar-b-que
directions: Cook beef until tender.
Cut into small pieces.
Add all ingredients together except beef and simmer 10 minutes.
Add beef and cook for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Keep cheeses at room temperature; mix all together.
Whip and roll into a ball.
Refrigerate.

title: chopped beef casserole
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in oleo until tender. Stir in flour and gradually add milk. Cook until thickened. Add thyme and cheese. Mix sauce with chopped beef and macaroni.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fudgy brownie
directions: Stir cocoa
and
baking
soda
in mixing bowl. Blend in only 1/3
cup
of
the
oil.
Add
boiling
water.

Stir until mixture thickens. Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup of the oil. Stir until smooth. Add flour, vanilla and salt. Blend completely. Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for
to
40 minutes.
Cool and frost, if desired.

title: shrimp salad(serves 4)
directions: Place shrimp and lemon slices in saucepan.
Cover with water and bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Drain and cool.
Whisk together next 4 ingredients.
Place shrimp and mushrooms in a shallow glass dish and marinate in oil mixture for several hours.
To serve arrange lettuce leaves on individual plates with an orange slice in center.
Arrange shrimp, mushrooms and artichoke hearts on top of orange slices.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer 1/3 of potatoes in buttered baking pan.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in a cup.
Sprinkle half over potatoes; repeat layers, ending with potatoes on top.
Dot with margarine.
Pour milk over potatoes.
Cover.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°, uncovered; sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except muffin mix.
Add muffin mix last. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Saute the onion, green bell pepper, celery, garlic salt and black pepper in 1 stick butter for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add the rice, almonds, mushrooms, beef consomme, beef broth and soy sauce to mixture. Pour into 9 x 13 casserole dish. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine the sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, 1 stick margarine, vanilla and milk and mix well.
Put into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to the top of the first mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp pasta salad
directions: Combine yogurt, seasoning, mustard, salt and pepper in chilled large bowl.
Mix well.
Add celery, tomatoes and green onions. Mix well.
Add shrimp and macaroni.
Mix well.
Refrigerate about 2 hours before serving.

title: spiced pumpkin bread
directions: In

mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add the pumpkin, orange juice, molasses and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients. Add to the creamed mixture and mix until well blended. Stir in nuts and raisins. Pour into two greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes. Remove from pans onto wire racks.

title: pecan pie squares
directions: Beat together the first 4 ingredients until crumbly. Press into a greased 15 1/2 x 12 1/2 x 1/2 jelly roll pan, bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for 20 minutes. Beat together the eggs, sugar, karo syrup, melted margarine and vanilla, add pecans, pour over the crust and bake for a further 25 minutes or until set.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Cook meat balls.
Cook chili sauce and grape jelly in skillet until jelly is melted.
Add meat balls.
Stir to coat.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Leave meat balls in sauce and serve with toothpicks.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Form into meatballs, about 30.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix ham, cheese, margarine, mustard, onion and Worcestershire together until well blended.
Split rolls and spread mixture on bottom half.
Top with other half and wrap in foil.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Can be frozen and heated when needed.
Makes 60.

title: gourmet pork chops
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
Melt a bit of fat in a frying pan. Coat chops in flour; salt and pepper.
Brown pork chops and place in a baking dish.
Combine soup, water, ginger and rosemary.
Pour over chops and sprinkle with 1/2 can of onion rings.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover.
Sprinkle with remaining onion rings.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Place chops on platter.
Stir sour cream into pan juices.
Serve over rice.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat together eggs and milk.
Add crumbs and corn.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add corn, seasoning and milk.
Mix well.
Dot top with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until firm and slightly browned.

title: mexican joes
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Put hamburger on bun.
Place on tomatoes, lettuce, cheese and onion.
Then put on salsa.
Cut up and "eat!"

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, butter, vanilla and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Blend in buttermilk.
Pour into pastry shells.
Bake at 300° about 40 minutes.
Pie should be very brown.
Yields 2 pies.

title: rice and broccoli casserole(preparation time: 20 minutes; cook time: 1 hour.)
directions: Mix all the ingredients except Cheez Whiz. Put in casserole dish and top with Cheez Whiz. Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: butter pecan frosting
directions: Combine brown sugar and cornstarch; mix in milk and corn syrup until smooth.
Add butter.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for 2 to 3 minutes, or until mixture boils and slightly thickens, stirring once or twice.
Stir in pecans.
Cool to desired thickness. Spoon over cake or other desserts.
Yields 3/4 cup.

title: baked ham salad
directions: Combine mayo, milk, mustard, salt and pepper; mix.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cheese; mix well.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Top with cheese; let melt.

title: oven stew
directions: Coat meat with flour, salt and pepper; toss with oil in a 3-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 400°.
Stir once.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple chunks (if chunks look big, I cut up smaller).

title: homemade croutons
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.

title: ham 'n mandarin salad
directions: Rub salad bowl with cut clove of garlic.

Combine ham, celery, onion, walnuts and orange segments in a bowl; cover and chill. Just before serving, blend pepper, mayonnaise, cream and vinegar; pour over ham mixture and toss until ingredients are well coated. Serve on crisp greens.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sushi
directions: Combine rice, water, sugar and vinegar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Turn fire down to low.
Cover and cook until rice is done.
Allow to cool to room temperature.
Toast Nori lightly by waving briefly over an open flame.
Place on a kitchen towel or a sushi mat.
Top with a thin layer of rice, leaving 1/2-inch at far end of Nori uncovered.
Along the proximal end of the square, line up your filling of choice.
Roll in jelly roll fashion, using the mat or towel as an aid.
Remember that 1/2-inch of the tail end of the Nori you left uncovered?
Dampen it with a wet finger and use it to seal your sushi roll. You should end up with a sausage-like black tube, the filling in the middle.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Spread peanut butter on cracker.
Place marshmallows on peanut butter.
Heat until the marshmallows are brown.

title: cucumber and onion dip
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers, chips and vegetables.

title: zucchini squash jam
directions: Add water to grated
squash.
Bring
to
boil.	Boil
6 minutes.
Add sugar, lemon	juice and crushed pineapple.
Cook (boil) 6 more minutes.
Add
apricot jello and cook 6 minutes. Pour into jelly jars and seal.

title: cottage cheese delight
directions: Mix cottage cheese, pineapple and jello powder together.
Blend in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mustard; mix well. Add milk gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil pasta until tender.
Drain and cool pasta.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl and add mayonnaise or salad dressing. Garnish top with grated cheese and bacon bits.
Macaroni salad is good served immediately or refrigerated until chilled.

title: snowball soup
directions: Cook 4 to 6 white potatoes until soft.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir.
Add soups; stir well.
Thin as desired with milk. Cook over medium heat until bubbly.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together in large bowl with cover.
Mix together vinegar, sugar, salad, oil and salt.
Pour this over vegetables and marinate overnight.
Drain and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream together the cheeses, garlic powder, onion powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Shape into a ball.
Put in freezer for 15 minutes.
Roll in walnuts and parsley flakes.
Will stay fresh for 4 weeks, if refrigerated.
Serve with crackers. Enjoy!!

title: brown sugar pie(serves 6)
directions: People will beg for this recipe.

title: canning vegetables
directions: Kerr tapered jars (wide-mouth pint, wide-mouth half-pint and regular half-pint) are especially convenient for freezing.
They are easy to pack and it's easy to remove frozen food without thawing.
All styles and sizes Kerr jars and caps are safe to use in the freezer.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients. Sprinkle top with nutmeg and set dish in pan of water in oven and bake at 400° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: casserole of corned pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lay chops flat in a small, deep roasting pan.
Sprinkle 1 3/4 teaspoons salt and the pepper over chops.
Cover and bake 25 minutes.
Meanwhile, in 1 1/2 teaspoons butter, saute onion, celery, green pepper and the remaining salt until onion is clear.
Beat egg; stir in the corn and crumbs.
Add to the skillet.
Stir and reheat thoroughly.
Prepare white sauce of the remaining butter, flour and milk.
Turn the hot corn mixture over the chops.
Pour hot white sauce over the top and bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes.
To serve, cut around the chops and lift them out with their topping of corn-custard intact.

title: thirst quencher
directions: Mix fruit juices and ginger ale.
Add honey, mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
Add ice cream; stir until blended.
Serve in glasses; top with cherry slices.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: smothered squash
directions: Dissolve bouillon in hot water.
Set aside.
Place squash and onion in pot and add dissolved bouillon.
Cook at low heat until squash are tender.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to boil on medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat; cool one minute, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Drop with teaspoon on wax paper or roll with a light spread of butter.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place your cocoa, sugar, milk and butter in a glass bowl and cook on High for 1 minute in the microwave.
Remove and stir with a fork.
Add vanilla, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix and return.
Cook for 1 minute on High in the microwave.
Remove and beat until smooth.
Pour into a buttered pan and cool.
It keeps great in an airtight container.

title: jack country beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Brown hamburger.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
If watery, bake another hour.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.
In small mixing bowl, stir together eggs, milk, butter and brown sugar.
Add to flour mixture and stir until blended.

title: celery almandine
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over low heat. Saute almonds until lightly browned.
Add celery, chicken bouillon cube, instant minced onion, sugar, garlic powder and ground ginger.
Stir until mixed.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or until celery is tender-crisp.

title: baked bacon
directions: Put a layer of brown sugar to cover the bottom of a cookie sheet. Place slices of bacon on the brown sugar.
Spread brown sugar over the bacon, coating as evenly as possible.
Bake at 300° until done, about 2 hours.
May take longer.
Bacon will get hard, like hard tack candy.
Cut bacon in 3-inch strips.
Serve cold.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients through food chopper and add salt. Let stand overnight; drain.
Then add the vinegar, sugar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Can in pints or half pint jars.

title: turkey meat loaf(serves 4)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and from into a loaf.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°, or until done.
Serve with gravy made from skimmed turkey broth, if desired.
Sauteed mushrooms may be added.

title: banana dessert
directions: Slice bananas and dip in lemon juice.
Mix other ingredients. Stir in bananas.
Pour in graham crust or serve individual.

title: jello salad
directions: Warm the applesauce.
Dissolve Jell-O in applesauce.
Mix together remaining ingredients and let set.
It will thicken.

title: 6 weeks bran muffins
directions: Mix the dry ingredients; mix wet ingredients.
Add to mixed dry batter.
Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Cook in muffin tins 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Mix will keep easily in refrigerator for 6 weeks.

title: cheesy potatoes ala verna
directions: Slice potatoes and onions like thick potato chips.
Separate onion slices into rings.
Place vegetables in a microwavable dish. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add water, cover and cook until potatoes are tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Put cheese on top of vegetables (enough to cover top of vegetables).
Cover and microwave just until cheese melts.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender with salt water.
Slice thin and drain.
Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: low-fat pasta sauce
directions: Steam parsnip, scrubbed and unpeeled.
Puree in blender with remaining ingredients.
Warm gently in a double boiler.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Spray Pam in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle rice over bottom of pan.
Mix together the three soups with 1/2 can each of water.
Pour over rice evenly.
Lightly (very lightly) salt and pepper chicken and place on top of rice and soup.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover and bake at 250° for 3 hours. Uncover for a little while to brown.
Yields 12 servings.

title: beef hash
directions: Stir together hot water and beef bouillon cube until cube dissolves. Saut potatoes, onion and garlic in hot oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat 10 minutes. Add beef; cover, reduce heat and cook, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Stir in bouillon mixture, salt, pepper, and if desired, parsley. Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Yield: 4 servings.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix all the above together. Add warm water to make a soft dough. Roll out like pie crust, use bowl to cut out around edge any size desired. Cook in hot dry iron skillet turning once. Makes about 2 doz.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add pineapple and pie filling.
Pour into oblong dish.
Chill until congealed.
Top with cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Cream together and spread on congealed salad.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: texas taco
directions: Cover large pizza pan with foil, then spread bean dip over foil.
Add sour cream, taco sauce, onions, olives, tomatoes, ground beef and sausage.
Top with cheeses.
Serve cold or place in 425° oven until cheese melts.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg.
Add drained beans; beat, then add dry ingredients.
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Bake in Bundt pan for one hour at 325°.

title: grandma dicke's german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes, not too much, but done.
Slice potatoes.
Cut 1/2 of a small onion on top of potatoes.
Cut bacon into small pieces and cook until yellow brown.
Drain bacon and place on top of potatoes.
Reserve grease.
Cut other half of onion into the grease over a low fire.
Place 1 teaspoon sugar and 1 tablespoon flour in grease.
Add enough water to make a thin sauce.
Add 2 tablespoons vinegar or more, if necessary.
Pour over potatoes.

title: lemon dijon dressing
directions: Dissolve sugar and salt in lemon juice combined with vinegar. Mix in mustard, garlic and pepper.
Gradually whisk in salad oil. Add egg yolk and whisk with wire whip.
Refrigerate 1 hour, then whisk with whip until thick.
Great on spinach salad with mandarin oranges and sliced onion.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread roll dough thin in a shallow cookie pan.
Bake according to directions.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, Italian dressing, garlic powder and sour cream together.
Spread evenly over crust.
Chop any vegetables you desire to use into small pieces.
Sprinkle on top of cheese mixture.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: melting moments
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy. Gradually add sugar until stiff peaks are formed. Fold in nuts and candy. Line pans with foil and drop by spoon fulls. Put pans in 350 oven. Turn oven off and leave in overnight. Store in air tight container.

title: sausage cheese puffs
directions: Brown sausage.	Drain.	Combine
sausage, grated cheese and grated onion.
Mix together and put by spoonfuls on top of triangle size croissant rolls.
Add
a
small
amount of cream cheese on top of sausage mixture.
Fold
up ends and roll into a ball.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake	in
oven, then reduce to 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Combine potatoes, butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and salt. Add baking powder, nutmeg and enough flour to make dough look like bread dough.
Turn onto floured board; knead, then flatten dough to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut doughnuts and doughnut holes; deep fry in hot shortening.

title: bread for bread machine
directions: To make dinner rolls or cinnamon rolls.
Set bread machine on dough cycle.
Take out of machine and form into desired rolls or loaves.
Let rise in a warm place until double in size.
Bake in 350 degree oven until brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: good and easy cheeseball
directions: Mix horseradish into softened cream cheese.
Form into a ball. Roll in finely chopped dried beef.
Make at least 8 hours in advance and refrigerate to allow flavors to blend.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Blend ingredients until smooth.
Add more flour, if needed. Spoon on greased cookie sheet, leaving room to rise.
Cook for 10 minutes at 400° or until light golden brown.
Yield: 10 biscuits.

title: swiss cheese and hot bacon dip
directions: Mix cheeses, mayonnaise and green onions (if using).
Spoon into pie plate and cook until melted and bubbly, about 20 minutes. Combine bacon and crackers; sprinkle on top.
Return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes 2 cups.
Serve with crackers.
Especially good with Melba rounds and bagel chips.

title: southern okra
directions: Place okra in a saucepan, add 1 in. of water.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 8-10 minutes or until tender. Drain and set aside.
Combine the next four ingredients, set aside. In a skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Saute onion and green pepper until tender.
Stir in sugar mixture and tomatoes, cook for 5 minutes.
Add okra and simmer until heated through, stirring as little as possible.
Serve with rice if desired.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and extract; mix together.
Add 7-Up last.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: egg rolls
directions: Clean and finely chop all vegetables.
Cook meat until done. Put all vegetables in a large pot with oil.
Wilt vegetables until done.
Drain in a colander.
Mix with meat and seasonings.
Cool until cold.
You cannot wrap while hot!
Place 1 tablespoon of mixture per egg roll skin and wrap as directed on package.
Use beaten egg to seal end of wrap.
Heat oil in deep fryer and fry until brown.
Drain, eat and enjoy!
Freezes well and is great for snacks! Makes 50 to 100 egg rolls.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, then syrup.
Blend well.
Beat in eggs; add milk, nuts, salt and vanilla.
Pour in a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° until knife tip inserted comes out clean.

title: seafood mold
directions: Chop peppers and onion.
Heat tomato soup to boil (undiluted). Mix cream cheese and mayo; add tomato soup mixture and mix until creamy.
Add peppers and onions.
Dilute gelatin in 1 cup water and add to mixture.
Add shrimp or crab meat.
Put in Jell-O mold and refrigerate.
Unmold.
Serve with crackers.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients together.
Put in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle grated cheese over the top and
bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: german's sweet chocolate pie
directions: Microwave chocolate and 2 tablespoons milk in large bowl until most of chocolate is melted, stirring once.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix well.
Shape into log.
Roll in chipped dried beef.

title: orange beef
directions: Cut beef into 1/8-inch strips.
Toss with garlic and orange peel in medium bowl.
Set aside.

title: spaghetti amora
directions: Lightly brown ground beef.
Add onion and garlic.
Heat soup and add cheese.
Combine the 2 mixtures with cooked spaghetti. Combine with meat; mix.
Cover with more cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Spread mustard on both sides of chops and flour.
Brown in oil. Place in baking dish and cover with soup mixed with water.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes, until tender.

title: mother's chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for at least 4 hours before serving.

title: beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease container.
Cook and stir beef and onion over medium heat until beef is brown; drain.
Spread in container.
Beat milk, baking mix, eggs, salt and pepper until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater. Pour into container.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef and onions until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Mix this mixture with spaghetti sauce.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Place cooked spaghetti in a large oven-proof platter; cover with meat sauce.
Top with pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Delicious!

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix and pour all ingredients into a deep-dish pie crust.
Top with a regular pie crust, leaving pan on.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove top pan and bake for 15 more minutes or until golden brown.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mix with pie filling.
Add condensed milk and pecans.
Fold in whipped topping.
Place in glass bowl and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Mix the items together and let sit for one hour.
Meanwhile, prepare chicken and barbecue until 90% done.
Dip chicken into the mixed sauce and put back on the barbecue for about 10 to 15 minutes, or until done.
This is enough sauce for 10 pounds of chicken.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and a little cinnamon.
Place 6 slices of bread on top of sugar and cinnamon.
Cover slices of bread with applesauce.
Place 6 more slices of bread on top.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over bread.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Chill can of Pet milk in refrigerator overnight.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar.
When mixture is slightly congealed, whip the Pet milk and gradually add the gelatin mixture.
Line bottom of large casserole dish with crushed graham crackers.
Pour mixture over crackers and sprinkle some on top. Let sit in refrigerator until firm.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Melt butter and mix in crumbs and seed; sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Wash, hull and slice strawberries, combine with rhubarb.
Add brown sugar, flour, white sugar and lemon rind.
Toss mixture lightly.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Fill pie shell and cover with top crust.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat eggs yolks; add 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix gently white mixture with yolks.
Stir in 1 pint each sour cream and milk.
Slowly add 1 cup (liquor).
Stir thoroughly.
Serve cold with grated nutmeg.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: baked zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs and oil.
Add the eggs and oil to the mixture and mix well.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: *Use only Hellmann's or Best Foods mayonnaise or it will not taste the same.
Use rounded measures.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Fifteen minutes before cake is done, make topping.

title: curried shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onions and shrimp in butter gently until shrimp are pink.
Add tomatoes, rice and celery (optional) and seasoning. Pour into greased casserole.
Top with bacon strips.
Bake at 350° until bacon is done, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper that have already been chopped. Cook zucchini until tender.
Drain, then alternate layers:
meat, zucchini and cheese in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with the cracker crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: chicken and cheese tortilla soup
directions: Combine chicken and chicken broth in large saucepan and bring to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and add corn, garbanzo beans, two cups broken tortilla strips, salsa & seasoning.
Heat mixture thoroughly.
Before serving, garnish w/cheese and remaining one cup of tortilla chops.

title: bean and corn casserole
directions: Partially
drain
corn and beans.
Mix together cheese, onion, water chestnuts,
soup and sour cream.
Place on top of vegetables and
mix slightly.	Crush crackers and place these, plus stick of butter, on top of mixture.	Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan bars
directions: Mix together and bake in long pan at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes.
Mix all ingredients; spread in lightly greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: In large pot, boil chicken until done.
Remove from broth.
Add all other ingredients.
Remove skin from chicken and cube meat. Add to vegetables.
Simmer until potatoes and cabbage are tender, approximately 45 minutes.

title: snicker bar salad(large)
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding until there are no lumps.
Add the rest of the ingredients and then chill.

title: timatar keema(ground beef-stuffed tomatoes)
directions: Wash and dry tomatoes.
Leave stems intact.
Cut 1-inch off the top of each tomato (save the lids!)
Using a spoon and knife, gently scoop out the soft insides of each tomato and reserve for later use.
Cover tomatoes and lids and keep aside.

title: mom's green chicken
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise and milk.
Layer broccoli, chicken, soup mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rahm pork schnitzel
directions: Pound cutlets as thin as possible. Season with salt and pepper.
Coat each cutlet first in flour (shaking off excess), then in egg and last in bread crumbs. Cook in 1/4-inch hot oil until golden brown on each side.
Pour off nearly all the fat from the pan. Add sour cream and heat gently, scraping up any brown bits from bottom of pan.
Pour over schnitzels.

title: grandpa tom's punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Turn into a large 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes at least 12 servings.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and top with a can of Durkee onion rings.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
(Can be made ahead and refrigerated.)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spicy oat cookies
directions: Blend margarine, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar, molasses and honey and mix well.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift baking soda with flour and add to creamed mixture.
Add milk, oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chip dip
directions: Beat all ingredients together, then chill.

title: grilled chuck roast
directions: Sprinkle meat with tenderizer, piercing with a fork.
Layer 1/2 of onions in large shallow glass dish; place meat over onions and top with remaining onions.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over meat and onions.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or for 5 to 6 hours, turning several times.
Remove meat and place on grill. Grill to desired doneness while simmering onions in marinade until tender.
Carve across grain of meat into thin slices; serve with onions.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: seasoned turkey patties(grilled)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Shape into patties and grill.

title: macaroni and tuna salad
directions: Add macaroni to boiling water; cook for 20 minutes or until done.
Drain noodles and add 1 can of tuna, then add the remaining ingredients listed in order and stir together.

title: pumpkin whoopie pies
directions: Cream margarine, shortening, eggs, pumpkin and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: wheat germ pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and sugar.
Add wheat germ. Combine the milk and oil.
Stir into the dry ingredients until just moistened.
Stir in cottage cheese only until mixture is slightly lumpy.
(If a smoother batter is desired, you may whip the cottage cheese with the liquid ingredients in a blender.)
Drop batter by spoonfuls onto a greased pan.
Cook until bubbles appear on upper surface, then turn and brown on the other side.
Turn only once. Continue until all batter is used.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: buckeyes(approximately 166 pieces)
directions: Mix peanut butter and butter together with confectioner's sugar till smooth texture develops.
Form small balls the size of buckeyes or large shooting marbles.
Slightly flatten. Refrigerate.
Next, slowly melt chocolate chips and paraffin together.
Using a toothpick, dip cold buckeyes in chocolate mix until 2/3 covered. Let dry on waxed paper.
The golden brown top bulges out over chocolate shirt and looks like a chocolate-dipped nut.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Parmesan cheese.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and dot with butter.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and let rise until it looks like a sponge, then add mixture of Crisco and sugar.
Beat together.
Add eggs and beat.
Add salt and nutmeg.
Add both mixtures together and stir.
Add flour in a large bowl and pour the ingredients in it.
Work like you would bread until dough is not sticky.
Cover and let double in bulk.
Pinch off hunks and roll flat about 1/4-inch.
Cut out doughnuts and let rise again.
Fry in oil.

title: delicious frozen salad
directions: Cut up marshmallows and put into can of crushed pineapple to soak up juice.
Pour pineapple can contents into a bowl and add 1 jar of pimiento cheese or pineapple cheese.
Put into refrigerator for at least 2 hours, until it sets.
Whip 1/2 cup whipping cream into bowl and freeze overnight.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onions, drain grease add spaghetti sauce in a simmer boil noodles until done; drain off water and layer all of these ingredients together.
Top it with the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix and beat 4 minutes with electric mixer, add 3/4 cup cooking oil
and beat another minute.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
After cake is baked and while it is
still
hot, prick all over the top with a fork and pour on topping.

title: snow salad
directions: Dissolve unflavored gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water. Add 1 cup boiling water. Dissolve.
Add sugar and vanilla. Stir.
Add sour cream. Whisk until smooth. Add Cool Whip. Blend until smooth. Pour in Jell-O mold.
Put in refrigerator for a couple of hours.

title: pineapple cream cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Fix pumpkin as directed on can.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish; put dry cake mix on top of pumpkin mixture.
Then cut oleo into slices and arrange on top; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: microwave fried potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes in thin slices and coat with butter.
Coat with Parmesan cheese.
Cook in microwave on High speed.
Stir and cook until tender.

title: grandma's anise twist cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients (not sugar) separately. Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Add 1/3 of the dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Add orange and anise extracts (more anise than orange!!). Continue to add remaining dry ingredients and orange juice, alternating while mixing. Refrigerate in foil or plastic 1 hour, up to 24 hours. Separate dough (size of a walnut). Roll in hands and twist. Grease baking sheet and place cookies on sheet. Bake at 350° approximately 12 minutes (check and turn at 6 minutes). If the bottom is brown, they are done! Cool completely before glazing.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large bowl, add all ingredients. Toss potatoes until they are evenly coated.
Place potatoes into 13 x 9-inch baking or roasting pan.
Bake stirring occasionally 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a ball (or place in a mold).
Serve chilled with cocktail sauce or use to stuff blanched snow pea pods.
Will fill 50.

title: chicken wrap
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly.
Rinse dried beef under running water.
Wrap dried beef around one piece of chicken.
Secure in place with a slice of bacon.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add water and bouillon cubes. Bring to a boil, add noodles, cook until done.
Add mushrooms and sour cream.
Place in casserole dish and top with grated cheese and brown in oven.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in 2-quart casserole.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix the flour and seasonings. Add soft margarine and mix thoroughly. Add cheese and Rice Krispies.
Form into small balls and flatten. Bake on greased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: marvelous mostaccioli
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
In separate saucepan, mix next 3 ingredients.
Pour over/into ground beef and simmer over low heat. In separate pan, cook noodles as directed.
Add brown sugar to beef/sauce mixture by sprinkling onto top occasionally.
Stir sugar into mixture as it simmers.
Drain noodles when done.
Mix noodles and sauce together.
Top with cheese, if desired.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix German chocolate cake mix as shown on box.
Bake 1/2 of batter in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Set rest of batter aside.
Melt in saucepan margarine, Eagle Brand and caramels.
Pour over baked cake.
Add rest of batter.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Bake another 20 minutes. Let set for at least 2 hours.

title: beans
directions: Cook beans as follows:
Add 6 to 8 cups hot water.
Bring to a boil 2 minutes.
Set aside to soak 1 hour.
Drain beans. Sort beans for any undesirable ones and discard them.
Put all good beans in pot with 6 cups hot water.
Boil gently with lid ajar until tender.

title: walnut cream fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan . Bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate.
Stir until melted. Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Spread in 8-inch pan and chill until firm.

title: country garden potatoes
