directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until just tender, about 25 minutes. Leaving skins on, dice potatoes into bite sized chunks and place in shallow casserole.
Moisten with milk.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and mash artichokes.
Add mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Put mixture into ovenproof dish and heat in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: spicy meat loaf
directions: Combine catsup, brown sugar and mustard.
Heat and serve with meat loaf.

title: turkey fajitas
directions: Cut turkey into bite sized pieces.
Throw all your seasonings on top.
Fry bacon and drain, break into small pieces and toss in turkey.
Fast fry in butter until done.
Throw in vegetables and top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and cook on high for 10 minutes. Dip tortillas in butter, just enough to make soft.
Layer 6 on bottom.
Pour meat mixture on top.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan and pour over tomato sauce.
Cover with 6 other tortillas. Shake Parmesan on top and bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Dissolve yeast in water; add sugar, salt and flour to yeast mixture.
Mix well until doughy.
Knead dough several minutes until dry and easy to work with.
Break off pieces of dough and form into pretzel, animal or alphabet shapes. Place on greased cookie sheets.
Brush pretzels with beaten egg and sprinkle with salt.
Bake in oven 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate waffles
directions: Beat all ingredients with wire whisk until almost smooth. Cook on hot waffle iron.
Remove carefully.
Serve with ice cream, peaches and strawberries.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mixture will be very thick.

title: italian queen cake
directions: Cream oleo, shortening, sugar and egg yolks real good.
Beat in vanilla and buttermilk, adding flour alternately.
Add nuts and coconut.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Cook at 325° in pan sprayed with Pam.
Cook until done, but not overdone.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Mix; put in casserole and heat in oven (350°) until it bubbles.

title: swedish yanazeti
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Saute onion in shortening until golden. Mix egg and milk; blend in Bisquick.
Add onion and half of cheese.
Spread dough in greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round glass baking dish.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese and poppy seed. Sprinkle melted butter over all.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot with butter.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt oleo in heavy pan, add peanut butter.
When melted, add sugar (1/4 package at a time).
Stir to blend well.
Remove from heat and add graham cracker crumbs.
Pour into a buttered dish. Cool in refrigerator, then cut.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Combine melted butter and lemon juice.
Combine parsley and cracker crumbs.
Gradually add lemon butter to crackers until you have a moist consistency.
You won't need all the lemon butter.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Grease and
flour
bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In small bowl combine
2	tablespoons
butter,
cream
cheese, 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch,
1 egg, 3 tablespoons milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Beat at high speed of mixer until smooth and creamy. Combine remaining
ingredients
in	large mixing bowl.
Blend well, 4 minutes at medium speed.
Spread 1/2 of batter in pan. Spread cheese
mixture
over
batter,
spreading carefully to cover.
Top with
remaining batter; spread to cover.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60	minutes,
until
cake
springs	back
when lightly touched in center.
Cool and frost.

title: cheese grits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add grits and salt to 7 1/2 cups boiling water gradually.
Cook until thickened.
Add remaining ingredients except paprika.
Pour grits mixture into oiled casserole; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield: 20 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1 cup crushed potato chips. Put in a baking dish. Sprinkle the 1 cup potato chips on top. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Place potatoes in large pan with 4 cups water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until tender; drain.
Add milk and vegetables to drained potatoes; bring to a gentle boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat.
Add cheese, butter and seasoning to taste.
Heat over low heat, stirring frequently, until cheese is melted and vegetables are tender-crisp.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: blueberry kuchen
directions: Grease and flour an 11 inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Then create egg mixture by stirring together egg, milk and cooking oil.
Add egg mixture to the flour mixture. Stir just until moistened and batter should be lumpy.
Spread batter in the prepared pan.
Arrange blueberry, sprinkle well with cinnamon sugar.
Bake slowly for 325° for one hour.

title: quick crab bake
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; omit salt; drain.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, cottage cheese, onions and parsley; mix well.
Layer half each of macaroni, cheese mixture and crabmeat in a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish. Repeat procedure and top with tomato slices.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: frozen philly dessert
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and corn syrup until smooth.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Freeze.

title: hamburger-cornbread casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion. Drain. Add tomatoes and beans. Salt and pepper to taste. Mix cornbread according to package. Add meat mixture to greased pan and top with cornbread. Bake according to cornbread package (approximately 20 minutes or until cornbread is done).

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine and drain fruits, reserving 2 cups juice.
Mix reserved juice, Tang and pudding until thick.
Stir in canned fruits, then sliced bananas and grapes.
Keeps 8 to 10 days.

title: meat ball casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, minced onion, Worcestershire sauce, milk, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Mix well together and form in balls.
Heat oil in frypan over medium heat and brown balls.
Remove balls from frypan.
Add 3 tablespoons of flour to drippings in pan.
If necessary add a bit more oil or butter to mix the flour.
Then add 2 1/2 cups (a No. 2 can) whole tomatoes and juice.
Stir and let simmer to get thickened.

title: chili and beans
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain fat off.
Add onion, vinegar, chili powder, tomato sauce, kidney beans and salt.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: walnut brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased 9x13 inch pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Check for doneness.

title: beefy cream cheese balls
directions: Shred beef in blender (save 1/2 cup).
With large spoon, blend cream cheese, onion and remaining beef and seasonings.
Shape into 2 large or 4 small balls.
Roll in reserved shredded beef.
Serve at room temperature with crackers.
Freezes well.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix all ingredients except soda.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add soda, stirring quickly.
As it foams, pour over corn and mix well.
Place on cookie sheets and put in oven for a few minutes at 225° to 250°.
Cool slightly and store in airtight container.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Remove shells from eggs.
Boil vinegar and seasonings; pour in glass jar.
Drop in eggs.
Cover and let stand at least 10 days before serving.

title: brisket
directions: Place brisket on large square of foil in shallow baking dish. Rub with liquid smoke and Worcestershire.
Sprinkle with other flavorings and spices.
Seal foil.
Bake at 250° for 8 to 12 hours.
This is tender and perfect.
Slice thin to serve.

title: david's quick and easy soup
directions: Put water, bouillon cubes and potatoes in a pot; bring to a boil and lower heat.
While cooking, cut up carrots and add to the soup.
While soup is simmering, clean and cut mushrooms (add more if you love them, less if you don't); add to pot.
Bring it all to a boil and then cook on low heat, covered, for about 25 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine soup, milk, mushrooms, half the onions, pimentos and black pepper in a large bowl and mix well. Combine green beans, half the soup mixture and chestnuts. Spoon into a baking dish; top with remaining soup mixture. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until heated through and through. Sprinkle on cheese and remaining onions. Let bake until brown, about 5 to 6 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and cool.
To cool spaghetti, add eggs, celery and cheese.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over spaghetti mixture.
Mix together.
Serves approximately 6.

title: ribs and beans barbecue
directions: Start heating oven at 350°.
Place spareribs in 3-quart casserole.
Mix soy sauce, honey and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Brush some of this sauce over spareribs.
Bake, covered, 2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oleo and stuffing.
Melt oleo and mix with stuffing.
Put layer of stuffing into pan.
Pour squash mixture over.
Reserve 3/4 stuffing mix to put over top the last 15 minutes.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or at 250° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: quick dinner quiche
directions: Add flour, spices, powder, egg whites and Egg Beaters in blender.
Blend 30 seconds.
Add cottage cheese and blend a little more.
Layer grated cheese and ham cubes in sprayed quiche pan. Pour egg mixture over ham and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until high and nicely brown.
Check with toothpick to be sure done through center.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Halve large pepper or cut off tops of small.
Remove seeds and membrane.
Precook peppers in boiling salted water for 5 minutes. Combine ground beef, rice, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Combine onion, egg and 1/4 cup tomato sauce.
Mix thoroughly. Stuff pepper and stand upright in a small casserole.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over peppers.
Bake in a moderate oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Baste peppers with sauce mixture 2 to 3 times while cooking.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix together and serve on toast or a lettuce leaf.
If desired, sprinkle with sesame seed and bacon bits.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour, salt and pecans; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Shape dough into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for about 15 minutes or until bottoms of cookies are light brown. Roll warm cookies in confectioners sugar.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: bee sting cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to instructions on box.
Set aside. Mix sugar, milk and butter together.
Cook in small pan until it boils for one minute.
Add nuts to syrup mixture and stir.
Pour syrup mixture into one 9-inch cake pan.
Spoon cake mixture over the syrup so as not to push the nuts to sides.
Bake according to cake box instructions.
Let stand 10 minutes, then take from pan.

title: abby's pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix syrup, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla.
Add eggs; mix.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over filling.
Bake pie about 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.
(If using a gas oven, the pie should be baked 45 to 50 minutes.)
If a toothpick inserted in center of pie comes out clean, pie is done (test after 45 minutes).

title: easy frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix and pack into an 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Cover with plastic wrap and freeze.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares and serve in paper cupcake liners or on lettuce on a platter.
Let stand 1/2 hour before cutting.

title: snowballs
directions: Crush peppermint candies in blender.
Scoop out large, round balls of ice cream with dipper.
Roll each in flaked coconut until completely covered.
Place on serving dish and garnish with cracked peppermint candy.
Insert a birthday candle into the center of each.
Return to freezer until serving time.
Serve with candles lit.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Place the 44 graham cracker pieces on a cookie sheet in a single layer. Bake at 300° for 10 minutes. After removing the crackers from the oven, raise the temperature to 350°.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Mix pineapple, cherries, sour cream, coconut and marshmallows together.
Stir in oranges.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours and serve.

title: lemon velvet
directions: In large bowl, combine cream and sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Blend in lemon peel and juice.
Pour into shallow pan (an 8 x 8-inch square pan is fine).
Freeze until firm (at least 4 hours).
Put in bowl.
Beat with mixer, then refreeze.
Serve in dessert glasses, lemon shells or boats.

title: chocolate-butterscotch bars
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Blend in vanilla and sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in chips and nuts. Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Cut into bars while still warm.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Dissolve lime in water. Soak cucumbers for 24 hours. Rinse and soak in cold water 4 more hours, changing water every hour. Drain well. Heat sugar, vinegar, pickling spice and cinnamon just until sugar is melted. Cool and soak cucumbers overnight in mixture. Simmer gently for 30 minutes. Remove spices and add turmeric just before packing into jars.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine corn meal, flour and salt; add milk, egg and oil. Mix well. Roll franks in mixture. Cover real good. Drop in hot oil until brown. Serve hot.

title: hearty bacon potato chowder
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add raw potatoes, cubed onions.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Add sour cream, milk, cream of chicken soup, corn (that is drained), pepper and thyme.
Continue heating until heated through for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: nutsies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then cream shortening and sugar.
Add to mixture well!
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients except oil in blender on mixing speed. Drizzle oil through top as the other ingredients mix.
Makes 1/2 pint.

title: venison roast
directions: Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix together and add 1 cup chocolate chips.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add in sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with whipping cream (beginning and ending with flour).
Mix just until slightly blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl.
Chill and may be transferred to 1/2-pint clean jar.
Be sure to keep refrigerated.

title: potatoes and onions
directions: Layer a buttered casserole dish with slices of potatoes, then add a few slices of onions on top.
Lightly sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Repeat this process until dish is full.
Dot with butter and add light cream to cover.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: baked spinach and artichokes
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Melt butter and mix with softened cream cheese.
Cut artichoke hearts in half.
Line the bottom of casserole with artichokes.
Mix spinach, lemon juice and cheese; pour over artichokes.

title: tallerina
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onions.
Add everything except noodles and cheese. Cook noodles until tender.
Into two casseroles, spread layer of noodles, layer of meat mixture and layer of cheese.
Then repeat layers.
this allows to complete layers in each casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Casseroles maybe frozen for later use.

title: potato and beef casserole
directions: Peel, slice and boil potatoes.
Fry beef patties in baking dish with potatoes on top.
Mix/combine margarine, flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Cook in a saucepan until hot.
Put in 1 1/2 cups chunked cheese.
Cook until melted.
Pour hot white cheese sauce over casserole and serve.
The white sauce recipe is from a book given to me by Andy and Elvina Garrett in January 1955 for my wedding.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except eggs.
Mix well and add egg yolks, one
at
a time.
Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: easy casserole
directions: Place beef in buttered casserole.
Add soup and water. Cover.
Bake at 250° for 2 hour to 2 hours and 30 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cheese bread
directions: In large bowl combine milk and yeast. Stir to dissolve yeast. Add sugar, butter and salt. Stir until butter is melted. Stir in 3 cups flour; beat until smooth. Add remaining flour and cheese; mix well. Pour into well greased 1 1/2 quart casserole. Cover with wax paper and let rise in a warm place until doubled. Bake in preheated oven at 350°
for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes. Loosen edges and remove from dish. Cool. Serve warm with butter.

title: linda's protein bars
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients.
Blend in the remaining ingredients.
Press into an 8 x 10-inch pan. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Heat over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, to the soft ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour in a buttered 8 x 8-inch dish or pie plate.

title: quick and easy omelet
directions: Mix. Spray bottom of skillet with nonstick spray. When heated, add eggs. In center of eggs, add omelet ingredients. Just as eggs of omelet get done, take spatula and fold in half and put on plate. The middle will not be done. Top with cheese and put in microwave on 2 1/2 minutes.

title: truffles
directions: In medium saucepan, melt 2 cups chocolate chips over low heat; stir until smooth. Remove from heat and allow chocolate to cool to room temperature.
Beat in egg yolk, cream and liqueur until smooth.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or until set.
Form heaping teaspoonfuls of mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: amish casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and brown sugar.
Season to taste. Add tomato soup.
Cook noodles and add cream of chicken soup.
In greased casserole dish, layer meat mixture, cheese and noodles. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese, add eggs and vanilla.
In midget foil cups, place a vanilla wafer and layer cream cheese mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool; top with Cool Whip and 1 cherry.
Keep refrigerated.

title: lemon cheese cake(lo-fat, sugar-free)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; put in blender the Jell-O, cottage cheese and cream cheese.
Blend until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip, put in pie plate and refrigerate until set.
Serves 4.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach (drain thoroughly).
Place in casserole dish and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine water, celery and onions.
Bring to a boil.
Then simmer for 30 minutes.

title: crab casserole
directions: Add cheese to white sauce.
Stir until well melted.
Remove from heat.
Add to beaten egg yolks gradually.
Add crabmeat. Turn into casserole. Mix butter with bread crumbs and garnish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry cream pie
directions: Line bottom of pie shell with berries.
Mix the whipping cream, sugar, flour and salt; pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat in small cubes.
Combine the flour, salt and pepper. Roll meat in flour mix.
Add few pieces to remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Bring liquid to boil, then simmer meat and mix together for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove from heat and sprinkle with parsley.

title: date-pecan upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat butter in a 10-inch ovenproof skillet or greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan in oven until melted.
Sprinkle evenly with brown sugar. Arrange dates on top so that each serving will include one. Sprinkle with pecans.
Beat remaining ingredients except whipped cream on low speed 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour evenly over dates and pecans.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Loosen edges of cake with knife. Invert on heatproof platter.
Leave skillet over cake a few minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: cashew pie
directions: Beat brown sugar and margarine together.
Add dark corn syrup, vanilla and eggs.
Beat until mixed.
Stir in cup of chopped, salted cashew nuts.
Pour into a chilled, unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Stir well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: new potato bake
directions: In small roast pan, cut new potatoes to 1/2-inch thick.
Layer at bottom of pan, slightly overlapping.
Add water just below surface of potatoes.
Add margarine, paprika, salt and pepper. Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven approximately 45 to 50 minutes.

title: southern smooth ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 4-quart ice cream freezer.
Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, mayonnaise and diced chilies to taste. Heat mixture over medium heat until blended.
Boil chicken breasts in water and chicken bouillon (optional) until cooked (approximately 40 minutes).
When cooled, skin, bone and dice. Pour 1/2 of the sauce over chicken; stir until mixed.
Spread a small portion of the other 1/2 of sauce in bottom of a casserole dish.
Put portion of chicken mixture in each tortilla.
Roll and place in dish.
Pour remainder of sauce over rolled tortillas.

title: ball game mix
directions: In a small bowl stir together Parmesan cheese, popcorn cheese, chili powder and sugar.
Set aside.
In a gallon size storage bag combine cereal and pretzels.
Pour oil over cereal; close bag and gently toss mixture until coated with oil.
Open bag.
Add spice mixture. Close bag and gently toss until cereal and pretzels are well coated.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 7 cups.

title: burgundy beef
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Brown beef and onions.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add thyme, wine and water, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches the boiling point.
Add parsley, carrots and bay leaf.
Cover and cook over low heat for at least 2 hours or until tender.
Add more water, if needed.
Serve with rice.
Serves 6.

title: wheat waffles
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat the egg white until stiff peaks form; set aside.
In another small mixing bowl, beat egg yolk, milk, oil and orange juice.
Combine flour, sugar, orange peel, baking powder and salt.
Stir into milk mixture.
Fold in egg white.
Bake in preheated waffle iron until golden brown.
Yield: 5 waffles.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.

title: horsey dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover.
Chill before serving.
Serve with Vegetable Dunkers, crackers or pretzels.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 1/4 cup cocoa, baking powder and salt. Melt butter. Add milk, butter and vanilla; beat until smooth. Pour into greased 9-inch square pan. Combine 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Sprinkle mixture evenly over batter. Pour hot water over top. DO NOT STIR. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Let stand 15 minutes. Spoon into dessert dishes, spooning sauce from bottom of pan over top. Garnish with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: creamy pasta with mushrooms
directions: Prepare fettucini as directed on package.
Drain and set aside.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Pat out about 3/4-inch thick on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into pieces.
Dip into flour and brown in small amount hot fat.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat with onion; drain.
Stir in flour.
Let fry a few minutes while stirring so flour browns on meat.
Add pepper, garlic and onion powders.
To this add 1 can cream of chicken soup and 1/2 can water.
Stir in sour cream; simmer for flavors to blend, about 10 or 15 minutes.
Serve over noodles, potatoes or rice.

title: veal von steuben
directions: Pound the veal cutlet until quite thin.
Dry well and season with flour.
Saute briefly on both sides in butter and remove from pan, but keep warm.
Deglaze the pan with a generous splash of brandy, adding the chopped shallots, mushrooms and heavy cream. When hot, put veal back in and heat until hot.
Serve over rice. Makes 1 serving.

title: choco-nut bars
directions: Soak raisins in warm water to cover until plumped; drain, discarding liquid.
Line 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 3-inch loaf pan with wax paper, allowing ends of paper to extend over sides of pan.
Set aside.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Blend other ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour these ingredients over the chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour (or until chicken is tender).

title: corn-on-the-cob
directions: Place vinegar and sugar in pan of cold water (enough to cover corn).
Bring to boil.
Add sweet corn.
Simmer until heated through.

title: apple-cream-crumble pie
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Prepare apples and place in large bowl. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and the nutmeg; sprinkle over apples, tossing to coat well.
Spoon into prepared shell.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Stir 1 cup boiling water into gelatin.
Add frozen strawberries.
Let stand until it begins to gel.
When firm, add ice cream and Cool Whip.
Fold in pecans.
Chill before serving.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into well buttered baking dish and bake at 350° until firm.

title: taco casserole
directions: Place in layers in a 9 x 13-inch dish as ingredients are given.
Serve with corn chips.
Great for a party!

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Mix and put
in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
I often put it in my crock-pot.

title: cheese and spinach puffs
directions: Cook spinach and onion according to package directions.
Drain well, pressing out excess liquid.
In a bowl combine eggs, cheeses, salad dressing, butter and garlic powder.
Stir in spinach and muffin mix.
Cover; chill 1 hour or until easy to handle.
Shape into 1-inch balls; arrange over baking sheet. Cover; chill until serving time or place in freezer container. Seal, label and freeze.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or 12 to 15 minutes for frozen puffs.
Serve warm with mustard. Makes 50.

title: old time biscuits(dedicated to minnie lee chambers)
directions: A biscuit bowl was always kept on hand.
We had a flour bin filled with flour.
The bowl was made by hewing out a block of wood then smoothed out to a fine finished by scraping with a piece of broken glass.
The more use of the bowl, the more successful the biscuits.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and put into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until firm.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix well and bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: stir-fried spinach
directions: Thoroughly wash the spinach and remove all tough stems. Shake off any excess water, but do not dry completely.
Set aside. Coat a large skillet with nonstick cooking spray, and preheat over medium-high heat.
Add the garlic, and stir-fry for 30 seconds.
Add the spinach and pepper, and stir-fry for about 2 min., or just until the spinach is wilted and tender.
Remove the skillet from the heat, and toss in the lemon juice.
Serve hot.

title: baked apples
directions: Pare,
core
and
slice apples.
Layer sliced apples in buttered
dish.
Sprinkle
a mixture of brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and	raisins
and dot with butter on each layer.
Cover with plastic wrap and bake in microwave oven for 7 minutes.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Discard cinnamon sticks. Serve hot.
Makes 14 cups.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes and mix with other ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 1 hour.

title: clams parmesano
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Saute onions in melted butter; add clams and milk.
Pour clam sauce over noodles; stir in contents of flavor packet.
Let stand a few minutes to blend flavors.
Toss with parsley.
Makes 4 servings (3/4 cup each).

title: cajun cake
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and pineapple with juice.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a 9 X 13 pan,
for 45 minutes or until done.

title: russian tea
directions: Steep for 10 to 15 minutes the teabags and 3 quarts of water. In another saucepan, boil together 1 quart of water, allspice, cinnamon sticks, sugar and cloves.
Boil slowly for 10 to 15 minutes.
Strain into the large pot of tea.
Add frozen orange juice and lemonade and pineapple juice.

title: grandmaw's green beans
directions: Take chopped onion and bacon and saute together.
Pour juice off green beans over onion and bacon.
Add vinegar and sugar; cook on high for 15 minutes.
Add green beans and cook on simmer for one hour.
Real good!

title: basic baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine; stir in flour, mustard and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens slightly (mixture should coat spoon). Remove from heat.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese; stir until melted.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cocoa cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium saucepan, melt shortening. Stir in cocoa until blended.
Beat in sugar, egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add nuts.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Immediately place a mint or chocolate wafer in center of each chocolate cookie and press in.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: plum muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into paper-lined muffin pans. Bake at 325° until lightly browned.
Makes 6 dozen minis or 3 dozen regular sized muffins.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix crumbs and 1 1/2 sticks butter or margarine (3/4 cup melted).
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together confectioners sugar, eggs and 1 1/2 sticks margarine for 15 minutes! (Important to beat correct time.)
Batter will be thick and foamy!
Pour mixture onto crust.
Layer pineapple and banana and spread Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries, walnuts and chocolate syrup. Refrigerate!

title: corn bread
directions: Add 2 tablespoons bacon drippings in a cast-iron skillet and melt.
Pour a majority of the drippings into corn bread mixture. Add about 1/2 cup of milk.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in skillet.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cool; remove bones.
Cook broccoli about 4 minutes; drain and chop.
Thinly slice onion.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, and lemon juice.
Layer chicken, broccoli, soup mixture and onion.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes. Serves 8.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in pumpkin, egg and vanilla.
In separate bowl stir dry ingredients; mix the two bowls and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Blend sugar and margarine until well blended, then add egg yolks, one at a time, then add flour, milk, flour and milk, ending up with flour.
Add baking powder and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold them into batter.
Also fold in 1/2 cup German chocolate.
Grease and flour pan; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot onion dip
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Stir together all ingredients. Place in 2-quart souffle dish. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with corn chips or crackers.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix strawberries and pineapple together.
Prepare pudding according to directions.
Bake cake by directions.
Slice cake in center (4 halves).
Put one half in bowl.
Cover cake with pudding, fruit, then Cool Whip.
Repeat for each layer.
Sprinkle with coconut, if desired.

title: taco corn bread pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add taco seasoning, corn and chili/salsa. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix corn bread as package directed.
Spread on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Melt margarine in loaf pan.
Mash bananas with a fork until smooth.
Add sugar, beaten egg and melted margarine (save 1 tablespoon in loaf pan).
Blend this mixture together.
add all-purpose baking mix and mix thoroughly.
Pour into loaf pan and bake 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm!

title: nanny's chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook chicken in slow cooker until done. Cool before deboning.
Reserve broth.
Prepare gravy per directions on package using chicken broth.
Layer 1/2 chicken, 1/2 drained peas and 1/2 gravy in casserole.
Cover with 1 crust. Cook at 350° until golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Layer rest of ingredients on top of this.
Cover with last crust.
Cook at 350° until golden brown.

title: asparagus salad
directions: In casserole dish, place asparagus spears, peas and soup in two layers.
Cover with cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Be sure to season with salt and pepper.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: raisin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat. Add raisins, spices and vanilla; mix. Add buttermilk, soda and flour; mix well. Add little flour at a time to make a medium stiff batter. Bake 50 minutes. Baking time depends on oven.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat the oven to 275°.
Combine the milk and corn meal or corn, and stir until smooth.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9-inch loaf pan or 1 quart casserole.
Bake for about 2 hours, or until set.
The pudding may be served hot or cold.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender, drain water and mash up.
Add cream of chicken soup, pimentos, onion, carrot, and sour cream; mix well.
Put 1/2 of Pepperidge stuffing in bottom of dish.
Pour squash mixture in dish.
Melt butter and mix with other half of stuffing; spread over top.
Cook at 350 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Mix all ingredients together except kisses.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Add chocolate kisses to middle of each cookie and bake for another 2 minutes.
